(4, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Living forms have some basic processes which help in the survival and perpetuation of its race, is called the LIFE PROCESSES.</p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span>$ \\star $ <span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;Nutrition, respiration, transport, excretion and reproduction help the &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; organism not only in its survival but also in its growth.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span>$ \\star $ <span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;Reproduction help in the perpetutation of a race.</span></p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Organisms begin their life as a single cell. In the multicellulr organisms this single cell ( zygote ) divides repeatedly and the resulting cells are organized into organs. These grow in size till the shape and size of the adult is acieved.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; single cell &nbsp;&nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ &nbsp;multicellular &nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ organs&nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ Adult body</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Organisms obtain energy from the food.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Plants are AUTOTROPIC , produce their own food by Photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ Carbondioxide and water are used for the production of glucose in the presence of sun light and chloroplast</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ Photosynthesis is the only process on the earth which can utilize the energy present in sunlight and also adds oxygen to the atmosphere and makes our lives possible.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;RESPIRATION plays an important role in releasing the energy stored in different compounds like carbohydrates that are synthesized during photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'LIFE PROCESSES', 'Living forms perform some important processes without which they can not survive :', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Living forms have some basic processes which help in the survival and perpetuation of its race, is called the LIFE PROCESSES.</p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span>$ \\star $ <span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;Nutrition, respiration, transport, excretion and reproduction help the &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; organism not only in its survival but also in its growth.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span>$ \\star $ <span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;Reproduction help in the perpetutation of a race.</span></p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Organisms begin their life as a single cell. In the multicellulr organisms this single cell ( zygote ) divides repeatedly and the resulting cells are organized into organs. These grow in size till the shape and size of the adult is acieved.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; single cell &nbsp;&nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ &nbsp;multicellular &nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ organs&nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ Adult body</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Organisms obtain energy from the food.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Plants are AUTOTROPIC , produce their own food by Photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ Carbondioxide and water are used for the production of glucose in the presence of sun light and chloroplast</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ Photosynthesis is the only process on the earth which can utilize the energy present in sunlight and also adds oxygen to the atmosphere and makes our lives possible.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;RESPIRATION plays an important role in releasing the energy stored in different compounds like carbohydrates that are synthesized during photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(5, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Photosynthesis is carried out by autotrophic organisms.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The mechanism of photosynthesis is simple organic molecules like carbon dioxide and water are converted to carbohydrates with release of oxygen by the chloroplasts in presence of sunlight.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Synthesis of any new compound from simple substances requires energy.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ The energy is required to form chemical bonds between the atoms of simple substances</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Reactant 1 + Reactant 2 &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\overset{energy}{\\rightarrow} $ &nbsp;Reaction ( intermediates )&nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ &nbsp;product(s)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; carbondioxide + water &nbsp;$ \\overset{energy}{\\rightarrow} $ carbohydrates + oxygen released by the chloroplast</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;Energy required for this reaction comes from sun light</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Green leaves are primary organs carrying photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;The green colour is due to the presence of a pigment called chlorophyll.</p>\n', 'Photosynthesis as a life process', 'Photosynthesis is the most important life process on earth which fixes light energy :', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Photosynthesis is carried out by autotrophic organisms.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The mechanism of photosynthesis is simple organic molecules like carbon dioxide and water are converted to carbohydrates with release of oxygen by the chloroplasts in presence of sunlight.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Synthesis of any new compound from simple substances requires energy.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ The energy is required to form chemical bonds between the atoms of simple substances</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Reactant 1 + Reactant 2 &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\overset{energy}{\\rightarrow} $ &nbsp;Reaction ( intermediates )&nbsp;$ &nbsp;\\to &nbsp;$ &nbsp;product(s)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; carbondioxide + water &nbsp;$ \\overset{energy}{\\rightarrow} $ carbohydrates + oxygen released by the chloroplast</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;Energy required for this reaction comes from sun light</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Green leaves are primary organs carrying photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;The green colour is due to the presence of a pigment called chlorophyll.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(6, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp; Photosynthesis is a complex process at the end of which carbohydrates are formed in green plants, using light as source of energy.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Photosyntheisis is a kind of Photo - chemical reaction.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;It is defined as a photo -chemical reaction during which carbohydrates are formed from carbondioxide and water, in the chloroplasts of green plants in presence of light.</p>\n', 'Defination of photosynthesis', ' Photosynthesis ( photo = light )', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp; Photosynthesis is a complex process at the end of which carbohydrates are formed in green plants, using light as source of energy.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Photosyntheisis is a kind of Photo - chemical reaction.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;It is defined as a photo -chemical reaction during which carbohydrates are formed from carbondioxide and water, in the chloroplasts of green plants in presence of light.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(7, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp; The equation of photosynthesis can be written as</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 6$ CO_{2} $ &nbsp;+&nbsp;$ H_{2} $O &nbsp;$ \\overset{Light, Chlorophyll}{\\rightarrow} $&nbsp;$ C_{6} $$ H_{12} $$ O_{6} $ + 6&nbsp;$ O_{2} $ + 6$ H_{2} $O</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ In this reaction observed that :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Carbon dioxide, water, light and chlorophyll are essentiial requirements for photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Glucose, oxygen &nbsp;and water are the products of the reaction.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;In the process we realize that low energy substances like carbondioxide and water are converted to high energy compounds like glucose.</p>\n', 'Requirements of photosynthesis', 'Photosynthesis require carbon dioxide, water, light and chlorophyll.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp; The equation of photosynthesis can be written as</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 6$ CO_{2} $ &nbsp;+&nbsp;$ H_{2} $O &nbsp;$ \\overset{Light, Chlorophyll}{\\rightarrow} $&nbsp;$ C_{6} $$ H_{12} $$ O_{6} $ + 6&nbsp;$ O_{2} $ + 6$ H_{2} $O</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ In this reaction observed that :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Carbon dioxide, water, light and chlorophyll are essentiial requirements for photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Glucose, oxygen &nbsp;and water are the products of the reaction.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;In the process we realize that low energy substances like carbondioxide and water are converted to high energy compounds like glucose.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(8, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Photosynthesis is the only process in which oxygen is liberated.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;We can conduct a simple experiment to show that oxygen is liberated during photosynthesis. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Take a few pieces of water plant like - Hydrilla. Keep a wide mouthed funnel into a beaker with water.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ Place the hydrilla pieces inside the funnel and invert a test tube filled with water over the narrow end of the funnel.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ Keep the entire setup in sunlight.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ After sometime we will observe small gas bubbles coming out of the leaves of Hydrilla. These bubbles collect at the end of the test tube.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ When sufficient gas is collected lift the test tube by closing its mouth with the thumb.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;Test the gas by introducing glowing splinter. The splinter glows and burns more vigorously indicating thet the gas escaped from the Hydrilla plant pieces is oxygen.</p>\n', 'Oxygen is evolved in Photosynthesis', 'The oxygen is evolved in photosynthesis , showing with an example using Hydrilla plant', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Photosynthesis is the only process in which oxygen is liberated.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;We can conduct a simple experiment to show that oxygen is liberated during photosynthesis. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Take a few pieces of water plant like - Hydrilla. Keep a wide mouthed funnel into a beaker with water.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ Place the hydrilla pieces inside the funnel and invert a test tube filled with water over the narrow end of the funnel.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ Keep the entire setup in sunlight.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ After sometime we will observe small gas bubbles coming out of the leaves of Hydrilla. These bubbles collect at the end of the test tube.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ When sufficient gas is collected lift the test tube by closing its mouth with the thumb.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;Test the gas by introducing glowing splinter. The splinter glows and burns more vigorously indicating thet the gas escaped from the Hydrilla plant pieces is oxygen.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(9, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Few experiments are conducted to show that carbondioxide, water, light and chloroplasts are required for photosynthesis. In all these experiments we will be testing for the formation of starch in the leaves.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In leaves glucose is converted to starch.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Starch is tested using iodine reagent. Appearence of blue colour on treatment with iodine reagent indicates the presence of starch.</p>\n', 'Starch formation is taken as an index for photosynthesis', 'Photosynthetic activity can be measured by using iodine test', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Few experiments are conducted to show that carbondioxide, water, light and chloroplasts are required for photosynthesis. In all these experiments we will be testing for the formation of starch in the leaves.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In leaves glucose is converted to starch.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Starch is tested using iodine reagent. Appearence of blue colour on treatment with iodine reagent indicates the presence of starch.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(10, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Light is one form of energy and it consists of tiny particles called photons. The energy carried out by photon is called quantum.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Light is one part of electro magnetic radiation. With increase in wave length there will be decrease in energy.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;The&nbsp;wave length of light that is absorbed maximum by the chlorophyll will provide more enrgy for photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Like a chemical reaction , the quality and quantity of each of the factors influence the rate of photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp; Light is an important external factor for photosynthesis and this can be determined by using a light screen test.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Carbondioxide is the most important requirement for photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ Carbondioxide enters through stomata into the cells of the leaf by diffusion. Stomata are present mostly in the lower surface of leaf.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ When stoamta are closed, the availability of carbondioxide decreases and photosynthetic rate is reduced to zero.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;We can conduct a half- leaf experiment to understand the importance of carbondioxide.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Leaves have natural openings in their surface epidermal layers for the exchange of gases. Use nail polish to obtain leaf peel to observe these openings.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'External factors', 'Light and carbon dioxide are important external factors of photosynthesis.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Light is one form of energy and it consists of tiny particles called photons. The energy carried out by photon is called quantum.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Light is one part of electro magnetic radiation. With increase in wave length there will be decrease in energy.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;The&nbsp;wave length of light that is absorbed maximum by the chlorophyll will provide more enrgy for photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Like a chemical reaction , the quality and quantity of each of the factors influence the rate of photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp; Light is an important external factor for photosynthesis and this can be determined by using a light screen test.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Carbondioxide is the most important requirement for photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ Carbondioxide enters through stomata into the cells of the leaf by diffusion. Stomata are present mostly in the lower surface of leaf.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ When stoamta are closed, the availability of carbondioxide decreases and photosynthetic rate is reduced to zero.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;We can conduct a half- leaf experiment to understand the importance of carbondioxide.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Leaves have natural openings in their surface epidermal layers for the exchange of gases. Use nail polish to obtain leaf peel to observe these openings.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(11, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp; Chloroplast is a definite structure containing different types of pigment molecules and chlorophyll is one among the several other pigments.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Green parts of the plants carry on photosynthesis because they have chloroplast with chlorophyll pigments.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Cholroplast occur mainly in the mesophyll cells of leaves. Typical chloroplast are oral shaped filled with colour less fluid called stroma.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Stacks of thylakoid membranes are located in the stroma and are connected by stroma lamellae.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Chlorophyll and other pigment are situated in lipid part part of the thylakoid membrane and organized to form the reaction centres called photosytem 1 and photosystem 2.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ By conducting &nbsp;variegated leaf experiment to show the importance of chlorophyll in photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;There are other factors like water , temperature, enzymes e.t.c which help in carry out the process of photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height:1.6em">$ \\bigstar $ </span><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;Water is an absolute reuirement for photosynthesis. It is from the splitting of water molecules that the oxygen is liberated during photosynthesis.</span></p>\n', 'Internal factors', 'Chloroplasts and water are essential for photosynthesis.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp; Chloroplast is a definite structure containing different types of pigment molecules and chlorophyll is one among the several other pigments.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Green parts of the plants carry on photosynthesis because they have chloroplast with chlorophyll pigments.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Cholroplast occur mainly in the mesophyll cells of leaves. Typical chloroplast are oral shaped filled with colour less fluid called stroma.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Stacks of thylakoid membranes are located in the stroma and are connected by stroma lamellae.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Chlorophyll and other pigment are situated in lipid part part of the thylakoid membrane and organized to form the reaction centres called photosytem 1 and photosystem 2.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ By conducting &nbsp;variegated leaf experiment to show the importance of chlorophyll in photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;There are other factors like water , temperature, enzymes e.t.c which help in carry out the process of photosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height:1.6em">$ \\bigstar $ </span><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;Water is an absolute reuirement for photosynthesis. It is from the splitting of water molecules that the oxygen is liberated during photosynthesis.</span></p>\n', 0, 0),
(12, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Photosynthesis involves</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;a) a series of oxidation and reduction reactions.</p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;b) synthesis of energy rich molecules like ATP and NADPH.</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; c) During &nbsp;photosynthesis chlorophyll molecule traps solar energy and gets oxidised</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; d) Chlorophyll splits water and gets back its electron from water</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; e) ATP and NADPH are formed during phtosynthesis</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ These all rections require light, therefore these reactions are called Light reactions of phtotosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Oxygen, NADPH and ATP are the end products of light reactions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Light reactions', 'Photo synthesis occur only in presence of light are called light reactions.\n', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Photosynthesis involves</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;a) a series of oxidation and reduction reactions.</p>\n\n<p><span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;b) synthesis of energy rich molecules like ATP and NADPH.</span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; c) During &nbsp;photosynthesis chlorophyll molecule traps solar energy and gets oxidised</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; d) Chlorophyll splits water and gets back its electron from water</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; e) ATP and NADPH are formed during phtosynthesis</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ These all rections require light, therefore these reactions are called Light reactions of phtotosynthesis.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Oxygen, NADPH and ATP are the end products of light reactions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(13, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Carbon present in carbon dioxide is fixed by a five carbon sugar Ribulose diphosphate and forms an unstable six carbon compound which is broken down into molecules of phosphoglyceric acid ( PGA ).</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;PGA &nbsp;is converted to glyceraldehyd - 3- phosphate which inturn is converted to glucose.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The series of reaction involved in the conversion of carbon dioxide to glucose discovered by Melvin Calvin for which he was awarded with Nobel prize. These reaction are called calvin cycle.</p>\n', 'Dark reactions', 'The reaction which do not require light are called Dark reactions.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Carbon present in carbon dioxide is fixed by a five carbon sugar Ribulose diphosphate and forms an unstable six carbon compound which is broken down into molecules of phosphoglyceric acid ( PGA ).</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;PGA &nbsp;is converted to glyceraldehyd - 3- phosphate which inturn is converted to glucose.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The series of reaction involved in the conversion of carbon dioxide to glucose discovered by Melvin Calvin for which he was awarded with Nobel prize. These reaction are called calvin cycle.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(14, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The life has a large surface to recieve more light has an extensive system of air spces to facilitate diffusion of gasses like carbon dioxide and oxygen.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Some of the plants like cotton and castor bend their lamina during day torecieve maximum light at all times.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Chlorophyll and Chloroplasts are the main photosynthetic organ of plants.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;A Leaf consists of three parts,namely Lamina, Petiole and Leaf base.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Internal organization of leaf is more suitable for photosynthetic activity&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;A typical leaf is covered by epidermis on both surfaces - upper epidermis, lower epidermis.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Epidermis is interrupted by a large number of openings called stomata and central opening is called stoma.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Each stoma is surrounded by two kidney shaped cells called Guard cells. stomata regulate the exchange of gasses and loss of water vapour from the leaves.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Leaves prepare food and support the life for all the organisms.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Leaf is the most important organ for photosynthesis.', 'Leaf is suitable to perform the process of photosynthesis.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The life has a large surface to recieve more light has an extensive system of air spces to facilitate diffusion of gasses like carbon dioxide and oxygen.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Some of the plants like cotton and castor bend their lamina during day torecieve maximum light at all times.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Chlorophyll and Chloroplasts are the main photosynthetic organ of plants.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;A Leaf consists of three parts,namely Lamina, Petiole and Leaf base.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Internal organization of leaf 