(39, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart is a hallow organ and it is situated slightly left side in the midddle of the thorasic cavity</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;It is made up of Cardiac muscle and it is conical in shape.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart is enclosed in a double layered , transperent, thin sac called Pericardium and between&nbsp;the two&nbsp;layers it is filled with fluid called pericardial fluid.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart is internally divided into four chambers - two upper auricle and two lower ventricles</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Large Veins that bring &nbsp;blood to the heart are called Vena cavae and Large arteries that carry blood &nbsp;away from the heart are called Aortae</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Right auricle recieves deoxygenated blood from the body</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Left auricle recieves oxygenated blood from lungs</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Left ventricle pumps oxygenated blood to body parts</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Right ventricle pumps deoxygenate blood to the lungs</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pulmonary veins bring oxygenated blood and pulmonary artery carries deoxygenated blood.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The blocking of coronory artery results in heart attack.</p>\n', 'Structure of human heart -  external features', 'Human heart consists of four chambers. ', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart is a hallow organ and it is situated slightly left side in the midddle of the thorasic cavity</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;It is made up of Cardiac muscle and it is conical in shape.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart is enclosed in a double layered , transperent, thin sac called Pericardium and between&nbsp;the two&nbsp;layers it is filled with fluid called pericardial fluid.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart is internally divided into four chambers - two upper auricle and two lower ventricles</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Large Veins that bring &nbsp;blood to the heart are called Vena cavae and Large arteries that carry blood &nbsp;away from the heart are called Aortae</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Right auricle recieves deoxygenated blood from the body</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Left auricle recieves oxygenated blood from lungs</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Left ventricle pumps oxygenated blood to body parts</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Right ventricle pumps deoxygenate blood to the lungs</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pulmonary veins bring oxygenated blood and pulmonary artery carries deoxygenated blood.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The blocking of coronory artery results in heart attack.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(40, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart has four chambers and ther seperated by walls or Septae.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Right and Left auricles are seperated by Inter - auricular septum and right and left ventricles are seperated by Inter - ventricular septum.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The auricles and ventricles are seperated by Auriculo&nbsp;- Ventricular septum and two openings in this septum called Auriculo-Ventricular apertures.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Valves of the heart allow the blood to flow in one direction only</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Tricuspid valve allows blood to flow from right auricle to right ventricle</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Bicuspid valve allows blood to flow from left auricle to left ventricle.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pulmonary valve allows blood to flow from right ventricle to pulmonary aorta</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Aortic valves allow blood to flow from left ventricle to aorta.</p>\n', 'Internal structure  of heart', 'Heart pumps blood and valves of the heart allow the blood to flow in one direction.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heart has four chambers and ther seperated by walls or Septae.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Right and Left auricles are seperated by Inter - auricular septum and right and left ventricles are seperated by Inter - ventricular septum.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The auricles and ventricles are seperated by Auriculo&nbsp;- Ventricular septum and two openings in this septum called Auriculo-Ventricular apertures.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Valves of the heart allow the blood to flow in one direction only</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Tricuspid valve allows blood to flow from right auricle to right ventricle</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Bicuspid valve allows blood to flow from left auricle to left ventricle.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pulmonary valve allows blood to flow from right ventricle to pulmonary aorta</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Aortic valves allow blood to flow from left ventricle to aorta.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(41, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Cardiac muscle present in the heart is responsible for the contraction and relaxation of the heart.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heat contracts and relaxes 70 - 80 times in a minute. The contraction phase is called Systole and the relaxation phase is called Diastole.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The path in which the blood flows is called circuit. There are two circuits for the flow of blood.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The one is between heart and the lungs called&nbsp;Pulmonary circuit and the one between heart and the organs is called Systemic circuit</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The pressure with which the blood flows in the blood vessels is called blood pressure.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Blood pressure is measured by an instrument Sphygomanometer. The normal blood pressure is 120 / 80</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The blood pressure will be very high more than the usual is called Hypertension.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;There are two components in blood pressure - systolic pressure an diastolic pressure.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Systolic blood pressure is higher than diastolic pressure</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Blood pressure in arteries is higher than blood pressure in ventricles.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Heart - mechanism of functioning', 'The heart recieves the deoxygentaed blood and supplies oxygenated blood', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Cardiac muscle present in the heart is responsible for the contraction and relaxation of the heart.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Heat contracts and relaxes 70 - 80 times in a minute. The contraction phase is called Systole and the relaxation phase is called Diastole.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The path in which the blood flows is called circuit. There are two circuits for the flow of blood.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The one is between heart and the lungs called&nbsp;Pulmonary circuit and the one between heart and the organs is called Systemic circuit</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The pressure with which the blood flows in the blood vessels is called blood pressure.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Blood pressure is measured by an instrument Sphygomanometer. The normal blood pressure is 120 / 80</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The blood pressure will be very high more than the usual is called Hypertension.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;There are two components in blood pressure - systolic pressure an diastolic pressure.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Systolic blood pressure is higher than diastolic pressure</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Blood pressure in arteries is higher than blood pressure in ventricles.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
