(43, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Substances like oxygen and carbon dioxide are to be transported with in the body.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Harmones need to be transported because they work at places other than where they are produced.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Harmones are the chemicals which control and co-ordinate the functions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Pituatory gland is located in the brain but the harmones it secretes work on the other glands like adrebal gland.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Transport system has undergone evolutionary change in animals.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In unicellular organisms like amoeba, transport of substances occurs within the cytoplasm either by diffusion.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Special fluids like blood and lymph were evolved for the transport of substances within the body of multicellular organisms.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Animals developed circulatory systems with blood vessels to transport the fluids. Arteries carry substancs to the cells and veins collect substances from the cells.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Need for transport', 'Transport systems are present in the bodies of all the organisms and they are essential to keep the cells alive and healthy.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Substances like oxygen and carbon dioxide are to be transported with in the body.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Harmones need to be transported because they work at places other than where they are produced.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Harmones are the chemicals which control and co-ordinate the functions.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Pituatory gland is located in the brain but the harmones it secretes work on the other glands like adrebal gland.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Transport system has undergone evolutionary change in animals.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In unicellular organisms like amoeba, transport of substances occurs within the cytoplasm either by diffusion.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Special fluids like blood and lymph were evolved for the transport of substances within the body of multicellular organisms.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Animals developed circulatory systems with blood vessels to transport the fluids. Arteries carry substancs to the cells and veins collect substances from the cells.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(44, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Transport system in Earthworms :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;There are 8 pairs of hearts in the earthworm which are placed laterally inside the body.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;The hearts conect the dorsal blood vessel and ventral blood vessel.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ Dorsal blood acts as a chief vein&nbsp;and Ventral blood vessel acts as chief artery of the body.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$&nbsp;\\star $ The blood consists of water, salts and cells.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ The coelomic fluid which is present between the body wall and elimentary canal also plays major role in the transport of substances in earthworm.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Transport system in cockroach :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;There are no blood vessels in cockroach and the blood flows in spaces called Sinuses.&nbsp;It is an Open circulatory system.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;In cockroach the heart is present in preicardial sinus, it has 13 chambers.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ The circulatory system in cockroach consists of heart, blood sinuses and alary muscles. The contraction and relaxation of alary muscles help in forcing the blood into the heart.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The two chambered heart in fishes evolved into a three chambered heart in amphibians and finally into a four chambered heart in birds and mammals.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In fishes, the blood passes through the heart only once in the circulation ( single circuit circulation)</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In frog and other higher animals, blood passes twice through the heart ( Double circulation ).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Nature of transport systems in various animals - Earthworm. cockroach and higher animals', 'The circulatory s