 heart ( Double circulation ).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(45, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ Living organisms recognize changes in environment and respond accordingly</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Animals, plants and bacteria respond to change in the environment. This property of responding to changes in the environment is called as Irritability.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Different organisms have different mechanisms to recognize the changes in the environment and then to respond accordingly.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp; &nbsp;Changes in the plants or animals in different stages of the life cycle occur as if some intructions are given to these organisms from time to time.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Co-ordination of different acivities in living organisms can be compared with a team game coordinated by a captain.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Coordinated effort between different parts of the body is required for an organisms to live.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Animals and plants coordinate their activities through perfect control systems</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Control and co- ordination', 'In Living organisms coordination of growth and development occur in an orderly fashion and also to respond to change in their environment.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ Living organisms recognize changes in environment and respond accordingly</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Animals, plants and bacteria respond to change in the environment. This property of responding to changes in the environment is called as Irritability.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Different organisms have different mechanisms to recognize the changes in the environment and then to respond accordingly.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp; &nbsp;Changes in the plants or animals in different stages of the life cycle occur as if some intructions are given to these organisms from time to time.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Co-ordination of different acivities in living organisms can be compared with a team game coordinated by a captain.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Coordinated effort between different parts of the body is required for an organisms to live.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Animals and plants coordinate their activities through perfect control systems</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(46, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Coordination of devlopmental processes in plants is through small chemical molecules.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The substances which act in minute concentration and coordinate growth processes are termed as Plant growth substances.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;There are five major types of plant growth substances AUXINS, GIBBERLINS, CYTOKINS, ABSCISIC ACID and ETHYLENE.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Plant growth and development are controlled by more than one growth substance, these substances work together or against one another.</p>\n', 'Chemical coordination in plants', 'Activities in plants are coordinated by chemical substances called harmones, these substances  may increase or decrease the growth.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Coordination of devlopmental processes in plants is through small chemical molecules.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The substances which act in minute concentration and coordinate growth processes are termed as Plant growth substances.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;There are five major types of plant growth substances AUXINS, GIBBERLINS, CYTOKINS, ABSCISIC ACID and ETHYLENE.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Plant growth and development are controlled by more than one growth substance, these substances work together or against one another.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(47, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Chemical substances formed in the shoot and root tips of plants is responsible for the regular growth.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Charles Darwin was the first to propose that plant growth is controlled by some sustances.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Oat ( Avena sativa ) was the first experimental material used to show the influene of chemical substances synthesized in plants</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;<strong>Auxins :</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;The Auxin usually refers to a chemical compound called Indole acetic acid ( natural auxin ).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp; Auxins are synthesized in meristamatic and enlarging tissues. Auxin promotes cell division in vascular cambium and it is known as root intiation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;The phenomenon of supression of the growth of lateral buds by the terminal bud is known as Apical dominance.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp; &nbsp;A large number of artificial auxins are synthesized . Auxin spray can prevent premature fruit drop.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Gibberllins :&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Gibberllin was first isolated from the culture of fungus <em>Gibberella fujikuori</em></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Gibberllin has significant effect on stem elongation. Dwarf rossete plants like &nbsp;cabbage and dwarf pea plants grow tall after treatment with gibberllins.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Parthenocarpy ( seedless fruits ) is induced in fruits like apple and pear with spray of gibberllins.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Cytokins </strong>:</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ Cytokins are produced by plants and capable of stimulating cell division and cell elongation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Cytokins can prolong the life of fresh leaf crops like cabbage, spinach. The levels of cytokins decrease in senescing leaves.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;They will also be useful in keeping flowers fresh.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Abscisisc acid inhibts plant growth</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Ethyene is the gaseous substance involved in the ripening of fruits</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Plant growth and development is regulated by plant growth substances which act together or inhibit one another</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Plant growth substances.', 'Plant growth substances may increase or decrease the growth.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Chemical substances formed in the shoot and root tips of plants is responsible for the regular growth.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Charles Darwin was the first to propose that plant growth is controlled by some sustances.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;Oat ( Avena sativa ) was the first experimental material used to show the influene of chemical substances synthesized in plants</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;<strong>Auxins :</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;The Auxin usually refers to a chemical compound called Indole acetic acid ( natural auxin ).</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp; Auxins are synthesized in meristamatic and enlarging tissues. Auxin promotes cell division in vascular cambium and it is known as root intiation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp;&nbsp;The phenomenon of supression of the growth of lateral buds by the terminal bud is known as Apical dominance.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\star $ &nbsp; &nbsp;A large number of artificial auxins are synthesized . Auxin spray can prevent premature fruit drop.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Gibberllins :&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\star $ &nbsp;Gibberllin was first isolated 