(48, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In animals different organs in the body is broght by two methods - by chemical substances called harmones and by nerve impulses.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Galnds are of two types - exocrine gland and endocrine glands</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pituatory gland controls the functions of all the other endocrine glands, therefore it is called as Master gland.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Some of the harmones secrete by pituatory gland - Growth harmone, prolactin, oxytocin, vasopressin etc.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Thyroid gland is located close to the trachea in the neck and it secretes Thyroxi.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The deficiency of iodine in food the thyroid&nbsp;size increases and it is called as Simple Goitre.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Parathyroid glands are close to thyroid glands and secrete a harmone called Parathormone which controls the levels of calicium and phosphate in the blood and bone</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Two adrenal glands are present - one on the top of each kidney and look like a cap on the kidney</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pancreas is a mixed gland - a portion of pancreas acts like an exocrine gland and another portion acts like an endocrine gland.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Endocrine pancreas secretes insulin and glucagon</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Testis secretes a harmone called Testosterone and ovary secretes two harmones - oestrogen and progesteron.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Chemical coordination in Animals', 'Endocrine glands secrete hormones in animals and hormones act on specific tissue.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In animals different organs in the body is broght by two methods - by chemical substances called harmones and by nerve impulses.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Galnds are of two types - exocrine gland and endocrine glands</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pituatory gland controls the functions of all the other endocrine glands, therefore it is called as Master gland.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Some of the harmones secrete by pituatory gland - Growth harmone, prolactin, oxytocin, vasopressin etc.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ Thyroid gland is located close to the trachea in the neck and it secretes Thyroxi.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;The deficiency of iodine in food the thyroid&nbsp;size increases and it is called as Simple Goitre.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Parathyroid glands are close to thyroid glands and secrete a harmone called Parathormone which controls the levels of calicium and phosphate in the blood and bone</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Two adrenal glands are present - one on the top of each kidney and look like a cap on the kidney</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Pancreas is a mixed gland - a portion of pancreas acts like an exocrine gland and another portion acts like an endocrine gland.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Endocrine pancreas secretes insulin and glucagon</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Testis secretes a harmone called Testosterone and ovary secretes two harmones - oestrogen and progesteron.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(49, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Endocrine glands can not repond to changes outside the body.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Nervous system can respond to the changes outside and inside the body through specialised cells called Receptors.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Nervous system may store this information for future use.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Human Nervous System', 'Endocrine glands are situated deep in the body and cannot respond to change occur outside the body.Nervous system can respond to changes inside and outside.', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Endocrine glands can not repond to changes outside the body.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Nervous system can respond to the changes outside and inside the body through specialised cells called Receptors.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Nervous system may store this information for future use.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(50, 'inline_html', '<p>$ \\bigstar $ Nervous system is made up of three componenets - brain, spinal cord and nerves</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Nerves acts as like wires in telephone - they carry information from various organs to spinal cord and brain and also carry information from spinal cord and brain to various organs&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Nervous system is made up of two kinds of cells - Neurons, and Glial cells</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Both neurons and glial cells are equally important for the nervous system &nbsp;to function</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Three distinct parts can be seen in all kinds of neurons - cell body, dentrites and axon.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ <strong>&nbsp;Cell body</strong> is also known as Perikarya or Cyton. It is the centre for all the synthetic activity</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;<strong>Dentrites </strong>are projections arising from the cell body and their number is highly variable ranging from one to several thousands . They bring information into a neuron.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ <strong>&nbsp;Axons</strong> are longer than dendrites and make contact with other neurons or effector organs</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Some of the axons also make contact with the cells in the effector organs such as muscles or glands and this site is called Synapse.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Axon<span style="line-height:1.6em">&nbsp;carry information from one neuron to another neuron or to an effector organ</span></p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;In some neurons, axons are covered by a sheath or a jacket called Myelin sheath</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;When a stimulus is applied to the neuron, a small electrical potential called Action potential is generated.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Nerves are bundles of several axons&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Efferent nerves carry information from brain and spinal cord and to efector organ.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigstar $ &nbsp;Afferent nerves carry information from sensory 