(51, 'inline_html', '<p>In vertebrates the nervous system is divided into three systems - Central, Peripheral and&nbsp;Autonomic nervous system.</p>\n\n<p>Autonomic nercous system has two systems - sympathetic and para sympathetic.</p>\n\n<p>The top layers of brain appear grey, it is called grey mater and deeper layers appear white.</p>\n\n<p>Grey matter has cell bodies and white matter has axons.</p>\n\n<p>Brain and spinal cord are covered by three mebranes. The outer membrane is called Pia mater, middle one is called Archnoid membrane and the inner one is called Duramater.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Central and peripheral nervous system', '', '<p>In vertebrates the nervous system is divided into three systems - Central, Peripheral and&nbsp;Autonomic nervous system.</p>\n\n<p>Autonomic nercous system has two systems - sympathetic and para sympathetic.</p>\n\n<p>The top layers of brain appear grey, it is called grey mater and deeper layers appear white.</p>\n\n<p>Grey matter has cell bodies and white matter has axons.</p>\n\n<p>Brain and spinal cord are covered by three mebranes. The outer membrane is called Pia mater, middle one is called Archnoid membrane and the inner one is called Duramater.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
