(53, 'inline_html', '<h3><strong>Natural Numbers</strong>:</h3>\n\n<p>Natural &nbsp;numbers &nbsp;are &nbsp;counting numbers, Natural &nbsp;numbers &nbsp;are &nbsp;positive &nbsp;numbers.&nbsp;The &nbsp;difference &nbsp;between &nbsp;any &nbsp;two consecutive &nbsp;natural &nbsp;numbers &nbsp;is &nbsp;always one.</p>\n\n<p>So, counting numbers 1,2,3,4,............ are &nbsp;called &nbsp;natural &nbsp;numbers , denoted by N.</p>\n\n<div class="content-formula">N ={1,2,3,4,........}</div>\n\n<h3><strong>Whole numbers</strong></h3>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;natural &nbsp;numbers &nbsp;along &nbsp;with &nbsp;zero &nbsp;are called &nbsp;whole &nbsp;numbers. It &nbsp;is &nbsp;denoted &nbsp;by &nbsp;W.</p>\n\n<div class="content-formula">W = {0,1,2,3,4,.........}</div>\n\n<h3><strong>Integers</strong></h3>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;natural &nbsp;numbers, their &nbsp;negatives &nbsp;and &nbsp;zero &nbsp;together &nbsp;are &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &#39;integers&#39;. They &nbsp;are &nbsp;denoted &nbsp;by &#39;I&#39; or &#39;Z&#39;</p>\n\n<div class="content-formula">&nbsp;Z = {...............,-3,-2,-1,0,1,2,3,.............}</div>\n\n<h3><strong>Absolute value of an integer</strong></h3>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;absolute &nbsp;value &nbsp;of &nbsp;an &nbsp;integer &#39;a&#39; &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;numerical &nbsp;value &nbsp;of &#39;a&#39; regardless &nbsp;of &nbsp;its &nbsp;sign , denoted &nbsp;by | a | .</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The symbol &nbsp;| &nbsp;| is &nbsp;used &nbsp;to &nbsp;denote &nbsp;the &nbsp;absolute &nbsp;value &nbsp;of &nbsp;an &nbsp;integer.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;If &nbsp;&#39;a&#39; &nbsp;is &nbsp;an &nbsp;integer &nbsp;then</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; | a | = {+a , when a is positive or zero,&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;=&nbsp;- a&nbsp;&nbsp; when &nbsp;a &nbsp;is &nbsp;negative}.</p>\n', 'Types Of Numbers', '', '<h3><strong>Natural Numbers</strong>:</h3>\n\n<p>Natural &nbsp;numbers &nbsp;are &nbsp;counting numbers, Natural &nbsp;numbers &nbsp;a