(68, 'inline_html', '<p>A digit or more than one digit being repeated in the same order , the recurring part is called the period.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Ex : 1)$ \\frac{1}{3} $ =&nbsp;0.$ \\bar{3} $ ,&nbsp;period = 3</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2)$ \\frac{7}{15} $ =&nbsp;0.4$ \\bar{6} $ &nbsp;, period = 6</p>\n', 'Period', '', '<p>A digit or more than one digit being repeated in the same order , the recurring part is called the period.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Ex : 1)$ \\frac{1}{3} $ =&nbsp;0.$ \\bar{3} $ ,&nbsp;period = 3</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2)$ \\frac{7}{15} $ =&nbsp;0.4$ \\bar{6} $ &nbsp;, period = 6</p>\n', 0, 0),
(69, 'inline_html', '<p>The number of digits in the recurring past is called the periodicity of the decimal.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Ex : &nbsp;1)$ \\frac{7}{15} $ = 0.4$ \\bar{6} $ , periodicity &nbsp;= 1</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2)$ \\frac{3}{11} $ = 0.$ \\bar{27} $ , periodicity &nbsp;= 2</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3)$ \\frac{5}{13} $ = 0.$ \\bar{384615} $ , periodicity &nbsp;= 6</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Periodicity', '', '<p>The number of digits in the recurring past is called the periodicity of the decimal.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Ex : &nbsp;1)$ \\frac{7}{15} $ = 0.4$ \\bar{6} $ , periodicity &nbsp;= 1</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;2)$ \\frac{3}{11} $ = 0.$ \\bar{27} $ , periodicity &nbsp;= 2</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;3)$ \\frac{5}{13} $ = 0.$ \\bar{384615} $ , periodicity &nbsp;= 6</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(70, 'inline_html', '<p>A number which can be written as&nbsp;$ \\frac{p}{q} $ , where p and q are integers and q$ \\neq $ &nbsp;0&nbsp;is called a rational number . the set of rational numbers are denoted by &#39;Q&#39;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Q = {$ \\frac{p}{q} $ : p,q belongs to Z and q$ \\neq $0}</p>\n\n<p>Ex :&nbsp;$ \\frac{2}{7} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-3}{2} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{7}{6} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{101}{2} $ ,&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{-4}{11} $ , 0.75 etc.</p>\n', 'Rational number', '', '<p>A number which can be written as&nbsp;$ \\frac{p}{q} $ , where p and q are integers and q$ \\neq $ &nbsp;0&nbsp;is called a rational number . the set of rational numbers are denoted by &#39;Q&#39;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Q = {$ \\frac{p}{q} $ : p,q belongs to Z and q$ \\neq $0}</p>\n\n<p>Ex :&nbsp;$ \\frac{2}{7} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-3}{2} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{7}{6} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{101}{2} $ ,&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{-4}{11} $ , 0.75 etc.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(71, 'inline_html', '<p>A rational numbers is said to be positive when the numerator and the denominator are either positive or negative integers.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Ex:&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{2}{7} $ , &nbsp;$ \\frac{-5}{-6} $ , &nbsp;$ \\frac{7}{8} $ , &nbsp;$ \\frac{-9}{-2} $&nbsp;....... etc.&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Positive rational numbers', '', '<p>A rational numbers is said to be positive when the numerator and the denominator are either positive or negative integers.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Ex:&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{2}{7} $ , &nbsp;$ \\frac{-5}{-6} $ , &nbsp;$ \\frac{7}{8} $ , &nbsp;$ \\frac{-9}{-2} $&nbsp;....... etc.&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(72, 'inline_html', '<p>A rational number is said to be negative if its numerator and denominator have opposite signs.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Ex :&nbsp;$ \\frac{-2}{7} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-6}{17} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{5}{12} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-9}{11} $ ,......etc</p>\n\n<p>Note : division by zero is not defined.</p>\n', 'Negative rational number', '', '<p>A rational number is said to be negative if its numerator and denominator have opposite signs.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Ex :&nbsp;$ \\frac{-2}{7} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-6}{17} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{5}{12} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-9}{11} $ ,......etc</p>\n\n<p>Note : division by zero is not defined.</p>\n', 0, 0),
(73, 'inline_html', '<p>Between any two rational numbers there exists uncountable rational numbers. this property is called the density property.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;The rational number lie between two rational numbers a and b is&nbsp;$ \\frac{a+b}{2} $</p>\n', 'Density prpoerty ', '', '<p>Between any two rational numbers there exists uncountable rational numbers. this property is called the density property.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;The rational number lie between two rational numbers a and b is&nbsp;$ \\frac{a+b}{2} $</p>\n', 0, 0),
(74, 'inline_html', '<p>A number which cannot be written as&nbsp;$ \\frac{p}{q} $ (p,q belongs to Z, q$ \\neq $0) is called an irrational number.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; The decimal expansion of an irrational number is non terminating and non-recuring.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Irrational number are denoted by&nbsp;$ Q^{1} $ or S</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Ex :&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{2} $ ,$ \\sqrt{3} $ ,$ \\frac{&nbsp;\\sqrt{2} }{5} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{10+2 \\sqrt{7}&nbsp;}{5} $ , 1.232342072.........</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\prod $ is defined as the ratio of the circumfrence (C) of a circle to its diameter(d)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; i.e. &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\prod $ =&nbsp;$ \\frac{c}{d} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\prod $ = 3.14159265358979............</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; The decimal expansion of &nbsp;$ \\prod $ is non-terminating non-recurring. so&nbsp;$ \\prod $ is an irrational number.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Note: We often take&nbsp;$ \\frac{22}{7} $ as an approximate value of&nbsp;$ \\prod $ , but&nbsp;$ \\prod $$ \\neq $$ \\frac{22}{7} $</p>\n', 'Irrational number', '', '<p>A number which cannot be written as&nbsp;$ \\frac{p}{q} $ (p,q belongs to Z, q$ \\neq $0) is called an irrational number.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; The decimal expansion of an irrational number is non terminating and non-recuring.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Irrational number are denoted by&nbsp;$ Q^{1} $ or S</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Ex :&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{2} $ ,$ \\sqrt{3} $ ,$ \\frac{&nbsp;\\sqrt{2} }{5} $ ,&nbsp;$ \\frac{10+2 \\sqrt{7}&nbsp;}{5} $ , 1.232342072.........</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\prod $ is defined as the ratio of the circumfrence (C) of a circle to its diameter(d)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; i.e. &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\prod $ =&nbsp;$ \\frac{c}{d} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\prod $ = 3.14159265358979............</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; The decimal expansion of &nbsp;$ \\prod $ is non-terminating non-recurring. so&nbsp;$ \\prod $ is an irrational number.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Note: We often take&nbsp;$ \\frac{22}{7} $ as an approximate value of&nbsp;$ \\prod $ , but&nbsp;$ \\prod $$ \\neq $$ \\frac{22}{7} $</p>\n', 0, 0),
(75, 'inline_html', '<p>The collection of all rational and irrational numbers is called Real numbers.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Real numbers are denoted by R</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; R = Q&nbsp;$ \\bigcup $&nbsp;$ Q^{|} $ or Q&nbsp;$ \\bigcup $ S</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Real numbers', '', '<p>The collection of all rational and irrational numbers is called Real numbers.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Real numbers are denoted by R</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; R = Q&nbsp;$ \\bigcup $&nbsp;$ Q^{|} $ or Q&nbsp;$ \\bigcup $ S</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 0, 0),
(76, 'inline_html', '<p>Let &#39;a&#39; be any positive rational number and we express&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{a} $ = b if and only if b&gt;0 and&nbsp;$ b^{2} $ = a&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; The value of &#39;b&#39; is called the &quot;positive square root&quot; of positive rational number &#39;a&#39; .</p>\n', 'Square root of a positive rational number', '', '<p>Let &#39;a&#39; be any positive rational number and we express&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{a} $ = b if and only if b&gt;0 and&nbsp;$ b^{2} $ = a&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; The value of &#39;b&#39; is called the &quot;positive square root&quot; of positive rational number &#39;a&#39; .</p>\n', 0, 0),
