\sqrt{b} $)($ \\sqrt{a} $-$ \\sqrt{b} $) = a - b</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;4)(a+$ \\sqrt{b} $)(a-$ \\sqrt{b} $) =&nbsp;$ a^{2} $- b</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; 5)($ \\sqrt{a} $+$ \\sqrt{b} $)($ \\sqrt{c} $+$ \\sqrt{d} $) =&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{ac} $ +&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{ad} $ +&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{bc} $ +&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{bd} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 6)$ (&nbsp;\\sqrt{a} $+$ \\sqrt{b} )^{2} $ = a+b+2$ \\sqrt{ab} $</p>\n', 0, 0),
(78, 'inline_html', '<p>A number is multiplied by itself again and again (repeatedly) , it can be written in a short form in exponential or power notation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ a^{n} $ = a x a x a x a x.............a(n-times); &nbsp; a- integer</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Here a is called base and</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; n is called power or exponent or index</p>\n\n<p>Law of exponents for real numbers :</p>\n\n<p>1)$ a^{m} $.$ a^{n} $ =&nbsp;$ a^{m+n} $</p>\n\n<p>2)$ (&nbsp;a^{m} )^{n} $ =&nbsp;$ a^{mn} $</p>\n\n<p>3)$ \\frac{&nbsp;a^{m} }{&nbsp;a^{n} } $ =&nbsp;$ a^{m-n} $ &nbsp; if m&gt;n$ \\frac{a}{b} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; =1 &nbsp;if m=n</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; =&nbsp;$ \\frac{1}{&nbsp;a^{n-m} } $ if m&lt;n</p>\n\n<p>4)$ a^{m} $$ b^{m} $ &nbsp;=&nbsp;$ (ab)^{m} $</p>\n\n<p>5)$ \\frac{1}{&nbsp;a^{n}&nbsp;} $ =&nbsp;$ a^{-n} $</p>\n\n<p>6)$ a^{0} $ = 1 , a$ \\neq $0</p>\n\n<p>7) If &nbsp;$ a^{n} $ =&nbsp;$ b^{n} $ , then a = b</p>\n\n<p>8)&nbsp;If &nbsp;$ a^{m} $ =&nbsp;$ a^{n} $ , then m = n &nbsp; &nbsp;if a$ \\neq $0</p>\n\n<p>Note :&nbsp;$ \\frac{0}{0} $ ,&nbsp;If &nbsp;$ 0^{0} $ are indeterminate form.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'Exponent', '', '<p>A number is multiplied by itself again and again (repeatedly) , it can be written in a short form in exponential or power notation.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ a^{n} $ = a x a x a x a x.............a(n-times); &nbsp; a- integer</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Here a is called base and</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; n is called power or exponent or index</p>\n\n<p>Law of exponents for real numbers :</p>\n\n<p>1)$ a^{m} $.$ a^{n} $ =&nbsp;$ a^{m+n} $</p>\n\n<p>2)$ (&nbsp;a^{m} )^{n} $ =&nbsp;$ a^{mn} $</p>\n\n<p>3)$ \\frac{&nbsp;a^{m} }{&nbsp;a^{n} } $ =&nbsp;$ a^{m-n} $ &nbsp; if m&gt;n$ \\frac{a}{b} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; =1 &nbsp;if m=n</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &n