(104, 'inline_html', '<p>At &nbsp;the &nbsp;elementary &nbsp;level , &nbsp;we &nbsp;can &nbsp;say &nbsp;that &nbsp;cell &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;composed &nbsp;of &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;or &nbsp;cell membrane , &nbsp;nucleus &nbsp;and &nbsp;cytoplasm. &nbsp;Some &nbsp;cells &nbsp;do &nbsp;not &nbsp;contain &nbsp;nucleus. &nbsp;They &nbsp;are &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;anueleated &nbsp;cells . &nbsp;The &nbsp;cytoplasm &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;fluid &nbsp;between &nbsp;the &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;and &nbsp;nucleus. &nbsp;The &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;outermost &nbsp;layer &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell. &nbsp;In &nbsp;plant &nbsp;cell , &nbsp;the &nbsp;outer &nbsp;layer &nbsp;is &nbsp;surroended &nbsp;by &nbsp;thick &nbsp;cell &nbsp;which &nbsp;is &nbsp;absent &nbsp;in &nbsp;animal &nbsp;cells.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>The &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;Membrane :</strong></p>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;or &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell membrane &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;outermost &nbsp;layer &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell. &nbsp;It &nbsp;allows &nbsp;some &nbsp;substances &nbsp;to &nbsp;enter &nbsp;or &nbsp;pass &nbsp;through &nbsp;it. &nbsp;Some &nbsp;substances &nbsp;also &nbsp;find &nbsp;an &nbsp;exit &nbsp;route &nbsp;from &nbsp;the &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane. &nbsp;So,&nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;or &nbsp;cell &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;is &nbsp;selective &nbsp;in &nbsp;nature &nbsp;regarding &nbsp;the &nbsp;entry &nbsp;of &nbsp;substances. &nbsp;This &nbsp;is &nbsp;why, &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;is &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;selectively &nbsp;permeable &nbsp;membrane.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Substances &nbsp;move &nbsp;in &nbsp;and &nbsp;out &nbsp;from &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell &nbsp;by &nbsp;the &nbsp;proces &nbsp;of &nbsp;diffusion. &nbsp;In &nbsp;diffusion , &nbsp;the &nbsp;substances &nbsp;moves &nbsp;from &nbsp;higher &nbsp;concentration &nbsp; gradient &nbsp;to &nbsp;lower &nbsp;concentration &nbsp;gradient. &nbsp;In &nbsp;cells , &nbsp;due &nbsp;to &nbsp;metabolism &nbsp;$ co_{2} $ level &nbsp;is &nbsp;increased. &nbsp;$ co_{2} $ &nbsp;moves &nbsp;out side &nbsp;and &nbsp;&nbsp;$ o_{2} $ &nbsp;gets &nbsp;inside &nbsp;as &nbsp;by &nbsp;the &nbsp;mechanisam &nbsp;of &nbsp;diffusion. &nbsp;The &nbsp;other &nbsp;mechanism &nbsp;by &nbsp;which &nbsp;water &nbsp;molecules &nbsp;perform &nbsp;this &nbsp;type &nbsp;of &nbsp;movement &nbsp;is &nbsp;called as &nbsp;osmosis. &nbsp;In &nbsp;osmosis , &nbsp;the cell &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;acts &nbsp;as &nbsp;semi-permeable &nbsp;membrane. &nbsp;It &nbsp;should &nbsp;be &nbsp;noted &nbsp;that &nbsp;diffusion &nbsp;does &nbsp;not &nbsp;requires a &nbsp;semi - permeable membrane &nbsp;but &nbsp;osmosis &nbsp;requires &nbsp;a &nbsp;semi - permeable &nbsp;membrane. &nbsp;In &nbsp;some &nbsp;circumstances &nbsp;the &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;operates &nbsp;to &nbsp;take &nbsp;the &nbsp;food. &nbsp;This &nbsp;is &nbsp;called &nbsp;endocytosis &nbsp;as &nbsp;it &nbsp;happens &nbsp;in &nbsp;Amoeba. &nbsp;The &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;is &nbsp;made &nbsp;up &nbsp;of &nbsp;lipids &nbsp;and &nbsp;proteins.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Cell &nbsp;wall :</strong></p>\n\n<p>In &nbsp;plant &nbsp;cells , &nbsp;there &nbsp;is &nbsp;an &nbsp;outer &nbsp;rigid &nbsp;covering. &nbsp;This &nbsp;is &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;cell - wall. &nbsp;It &nbsp;is &nbsp;made &nbsp;of &nbsp;cellulose. &nbsp;Due &nbsp;to &nbsp;the &nbsp;presence &nbsp;of &nbsp;cell - wall , &nbsp;regidity of &nbsp;the &nbsp;plant &nbsp;structure &nbsp;is &nbsp;maintained.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;In &nbsp;some &nbsp;circumstances , &nbsp;the &nbsp;plant &nbsp;cell &nbsp;loses &nbsp;water &nbsp;from &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell - wall. This &nbsp;is &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;plasmolysis.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Nucleus :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Nucleus &nbsp;is &nbsp;one &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;prominent &nbsp;organelles &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell. It &nbsp;is &nbsp;covered &nbsp;by &nbsp;a &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;called &nbsp;nuclear membrane. &nbsp;Nuclear &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;also &nbsp;contains pores &nbsp;for &nbsp;allowing &nbsp;the &nbsp;substances &nbsp;to &nbsp;pass &nbsp;through &nbsp;it. &nbsp;Prokaryotic &nbsp;organisms &nbsp;do &nbsp;not &nbsp;have &nbsp;a &nbsp;organised &nbsp;nucleus. &nbsp;Nucleus &nbsp;contains &nbsp;chromosomes &nbsp;in &nbsp;which &nbsp;DNA &nbsp;( Deoxyribo &nbsp;Nucleic &nbsp;Acid ) &nbsp;makes &nbsp;a &nbsp;packing &nbsp;structure &nbsp;along &nbsp;with &nbsp;proteins. &nbsp;In &nbsp;a &nbsp;non - dividing &nbsp;cell , &nbsp;The &nbsp;DNA &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;part &nbsp;of &nbsp;chromatin &nbsp;material.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Nucleus &nbsp;has &nbsp;crucial &nbsp;role &nbsp;in &nbsp;cell - division. &nbsp;It &nbsp;also &nbsp;controls &nbsp;a &nbsp;majority &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;cellular &nbsp;activities. &nbsp;Nucleus &nbsp;contains &nbsp;chromosomes/ DNA &nbsp;which &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;genetic &nbsp;meterial &nbsp;in &nbsp;most &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;organisms.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Cytoplasm :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Cytoplasm &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;fluid &nbsp;part &nbsp;between &nbsp;the &nbsp;nucleus &nbsp;and &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell-wall. There &nbsp;are &nbsp;many &nbsp;cytoplasmic &nbsp;organelles &nbsp;present &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;cytoplasm. &nbsp;In &nbsp;prokaryotes , &nbsp;organelles &nbsp;which &nbsp;have &nbsp;an &nbsp;outer &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;are &nbsp;absent. &nbsp;Eukaryotes &nbsp;have &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;bound &nbsp;organelles .</p>\n\n<p><strong>The &nbsp;different &nbsp;cell &nbsp;organelles &nbsp;in &nbsp;an &nbsp;eukaryotic &nbsp;cell :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Eukaryotic &nbsp;cells &nbsp;contain &nbsp;membrane - bound &nbsp;organelles. &nbsp;Some &nbsp;organelles &nbsp;are &nbsp;specific &nbsp;to &nbsp;plants &nbsp;and &nbsp;animal &nbsp;cells. &nbsp;For &nbsp;example , &nbsp;chloroplast &nbsp;is &nbsp;present &nbsp;in &nbsp;plant &nbsp;cells &nbsp;only &nbsp;and &nbsp; centriole &nbsp;is &nbsp;present &nbsp;in &nbsp;animal &nbsp;cell &nbsp;only. &nbsp;Some &nbsp;important &nbsp;cell &nbsp;organelles &nbsp;and &nbsp;their &nbsp;function&nbsp;&nbsp;arre &nbsp;as &nbsp;follow&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>a) Endoplasmic &nbsp;Reticulum ( ER ) :</strong></p>\n\n<p>These &nbsp;are &nbsp;tubular &nbsp;structures. &nbsp;According &nbsp;to &nbsp;the &nbsp;presence &nbsp;of &nbsp;ribosomes , &nbsp;ER &nbsp;are classified &nbsp;as &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>SER &nbsp;( Smooth &nbsp;endoplasmic &nbsp;reticulum )</p>\n\n<p>RER &nbsp;( Rough&nbsp;endoplasmic &nbsp;reticulum )</p>\n\n<p>RER &nbsp;contains &nbsp;ribosomes &nbsp;and &nbsp;hence &nbsp;it &nbsp;look &nbsp;rough. The &nbsp;endoplasmic &nbsp;reticulum &nbsp;helps &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;transport &nbsp;of &nbsp;proteins &nbsp;between &nbsp;cytoplasm &nbsp;and &nbsp;nucleus. &nbsp;SER &nbsp;helps &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;manufacturing&nbsp; process &nbsp;of &nbsp;fats &nbsp;and &nbsp;lipids &nbsp;and &nbsp;help &nbsp;indirectly &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;process &nbsp;of &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;biogenesis. &nbsp;Membrane &nbsp;biogenesis &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;process &nbsp;of &nbsp;building &nbsp;of &nbsp;cell &nbsp;membrane. &nbsp;ER &nbsp;always &nbsp;forms &nbsp;a &nbsp;network. &nbsp;SER &nbsp;also &nbsp;helps &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;defoxification &nbsp;process.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>b) Golgi &nbsp;bodies :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Golgi - bodies &nbsp;or &nbsp;Golgi - complex &nbsp;or &nbsp;Golgi &nbsp;apparates &nbsp;are &nbsp;membrane - bound &nbsp;vesicles &nbsp;which &nbsp;are &nbsp;arranged &nbsp;as &nbsp;parallel &nbsp;tracks. &nbsp;These &nbsp;parallel &nbsp;tracks &nbsp;are &nbsp;like &nbsp;stacks &nbsp;and &nbsp;are &nbsp;called as &nbsp;cisterns. &nbsp;The &nbsp;main &nbsp;functions &nbsp;of &nbsp;golgi &nbsp;complex &nbsp;are &nbsp;storage &nbsp;of &nbsp;products &nbsp;like &nbsp;sugars. &nbsp;Golgi &nbsp;bodies &nbsp;also &nbsp;help &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;formation &nbsp;of &nbsp;lysosomes.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>c) Lysosomes :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Lysosomes &nbsp;are &nbsp;regarded &nbsp;as &nbsp;suicidal &nbsp;bags. &nbsp;They &nbsp;help &nbsp;in &nbsp;digesting &nbsp;foreign &nbsp;materials &nbsp;as &nbsp;damaged &nbsp;cell - organelles. They &nbsp;are &nbsp;able &nbsp;to &nbsp;perform &nbsp;this &nbsp;type &nbsp;of &nbsp;activity &nbsp;as &nbsp;they &nbsp;contain &nbsp;strong &nbsp;digesting &nbsp;enzymes. &nbsp;Lysosomes &nbsp;are &nbsp;as &nbsp;suicidal &nbsp;bags &nbsp;because &nbsp;they &nbsp;can &nbsp;digest &nbsp;their &nbsp;own &nbsp;cell , &nbsp;if &nbsp;damaged.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>d) Mitochondria :&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>Mitochondria &nbsp;are &nbsp;regarded &nbsp;as &nbsp;powerhouse &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell. &nbsp;They &nbsp;are &nbsp;many &nbsp;mitochondria &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell. &nbsp;The &nbsp;singular &nbsp;of &nbsp;mitochondria &nbsp;is &nbsp;mitochondrion.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; The &nbsp;prime &nbsp;function &nbsp;of &nbsp;mitochondria &nbsp;is &nbsp;to &nbsp;release &nbsp;energy &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;form &nbsp;of &nbsp;ATP &nbsp; ( Adenosine &nbsp;triphosphate ). &nbsp;The &nbsp;inner - &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;mitochondria &nbsp;is &nbsp;folded &nbsp;and &nbsp;is &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;cisternae. &nbsp;In &nbsp;this &nbsp;place , ATP - generation &nbsp;takes place. Some &nbsp;mitochondria &nbsp;have &nbsp;DNA &nbsp;which &nbsp;help &nbsp;them &nbsp;to &nbsp;make &nbsp;proteins.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>e) Plastids :&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>These &nbsp;are &nbsp;the &nbsp;organelles &nbsp;specific &nbsp;to &nbsp;plant &nbsp;cells. &nbsp;The &nbsp;coloured &nbsp;plastids &nbsp;are &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;chromoplasts , &nbsp;while &nbsp;the &nbsp;white &nbsp;plastids &nbsp;are &nbsp;termed &nbsp;as &nbsp;leucoplasts. &nbsp;Plastids &nbsp;contain &nbsp;chlorophyll &nbsp;which &nbsp;help &nbsp;in &nbsp;photosynthesis. &nbsp;Leucoplast &nbsp;help &nbsp;in &nbsp;storing &nbsp;plastids &nbsp;have &nbsp;DNA &nbsp;too.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>f) Vacuoles :</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Large &nbsp;vacoules &nbsp;are &nbsp;present &nbsp;in &nbsp;plant &nbsp;cell. &nbsp;They &nbsp;store &nbsp;water, &nbsp;amino &nbsp;acids , &nbsp;sugars , &nbsp;proteins &nbsp;etc... &nbsp;which &nbsp;are &nbsp;used &nbsp;by &nbsp;the &nbsp;plant &nbsp;for &nbsp;performing &nbsp;different &nbsp;functins. &nbsp;Vacuoles &nbsp;also &nbsp;provide &nbsp;turgidity &nbsp;and &nbsp;rigidity &nbsp;to &nbsp;cell.</p>\n\n<p>Thus , cell &nbsp;as a &nbsp;unit &nbsp;carries &nbsp;out &nbsp;every &nbsp;function &nbsp;necessary &nbsp;for &nbsp;life &nbsp;process. &nbsp;So , it &nbsp;the &nbsp;fundamental &nbsp;or &nbsp;basic &nbsp;unit &nbsp;of &nbsp;life.</p>\n', 'Different   cell  organelles  and  their  functions', '', '<p>At &nbsp;the &nbsp;elementary &nbsp;level , &nbsp;we &nbsp;can &nbsp;say &nbsp;that &nbsp;cell &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;composed &nbsp;of &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;or &nbsp;cell membrane , &nbsp;nucleus &nbsp;and &nbsp;cytoplasm. &nbsp;Some &nbsp;cells &nbsp;do &nbsp;not &nbsp;contain &nbsp;nucleus. &nbsp;They &nbsp;are &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;anueleated &nbsp;cells . &nbsp;The &nbsp;cytoplasm &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;fluid &nbsp;between &nbsp;the &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;and &nbsp;nucleus. &nbsp;The &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;outermost &nbsp;layer &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;cell. &nbsp;In &nbsp;plant &nbsp;cell , &nbsp;the &nbsp;outer &nbsp;layer &nbsp;is &nbsp;surroended &nbsp;by &nbsp;thick &nbsp;cell &nbsp;which &nbsp;is &nbsp;absent &nbsp;in &nbsp;animal &nbsp;cells.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>The &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;Membrane :</strong></p>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;plasma &nbsp;membrane &nbsp;or &nbsp;the &nbsp;c