(107, 'inline_html', '<p>Animal &nbsp;tissues &nbsp;are &nbsp;different &nbsp;from &nbsp;plant &nbsp;tissues. &nbsp;There &nbsp;are &nbsp;different &nbsp;types &nbsp;of &nbsp;animal &nbsp;tissues, &nbsp;and &nbsp;they &nbsp;differ &nbsp;in &nbsp;structure &nbsp;and &nbsp;function. &nbsp;The &nbsp;different &nbsp;animal &nbsp;tissues &nbsp;and &nbsp;their &nbsp;functions &nbsp;are &nbsp;given &nbsp;below.</p>\n\n<p><strong>a) Epithetial &nbsp;tissue :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Epithetial &nbsp;tissues &nbsp;from &nbsp;the &nbsp;outer wvering &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;animal &nbsp;cell. &nbsp;It &nbsp;is &nbsp;found &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;outer &nbsp;skin &nbsp;to &nbsp;the &nbsp;linings &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;blood &nbsp;vessels. &nbsp;Epithelial &nbsp;cells &nbsp;are &nbsp;tightly - packed &nbsp;cells &nbsp;and &nbsp;do &nbsp;not &nbsp;allow &nbsp;all &nbsp;the &nbsp;materials &nbsp;to &nbsp;pass &nbsp;through &nbsp;it. &nbsp;There &nbsp;are &nbsp;mainly &nbsp;four &nbsp;types &nbsp;of &nbsp;epithelial &nbsp;tissue ; &nbsp;All &nbsp;lie &nbsp;on &nbsp;a &nbsp;basement &nbsp;membrane. &nbsp;The &nbsp;four &nbsp;types &nbsp;of &nbsp;epithelium &nbsp;are :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>1) Squamous &nbsp;epithelium :&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;These &nbsp;are &nbsp;flat &nbsp;and &nbsp;thin &nbsp;cells. &nbsp;They &nbsp;form &nbsp;the &nbsp;lining &nbsp;of &nbsp;important &nbsp;organs (skin, mouth etc.) &nbsp;In &nbsp;skin , the &nbsp;squamous &nbsp;cells &nbsp;are &nbsp;arranged &nbsp;in &nbsp;layers &nbsp;and &nbsp;hence &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;stratified &nbsp;squamous &nbsp;epithelium.</p>\n\n<p><strong>2) Columnar &nbsp;epithelium :</strong></p>\n\n<p>These &nbsp;cells &nbsp;are &nbsp;fall &nbsp;and &nbsp;appear &nbsp;as &nbsp;column &nbsp;and &nbsp;often &nbsp;bear &nbsp;clia &nbsp;and &nbsp;fagella. &nbsp;They &nbsp;form &nbsp;the &nbsp;inner &nbsp;lining &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;respiratory &nbsp;track. &nbsp;The &nbsp;clia &nbsp;contains &nbsp;columnar &nbsp;cell &nbsp;is &nbsp;called &nbsp;ciliated &nbsp;colermnar &nbsp;epithelium.</p>\n\n<p><strong>3) Cuboidal &nbsp;epithelium :</strong></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;These &nbsp;are &nbsp;the &nbsp;third &nbsp;type &nbsp;of &nbsp;epithelial &nbsp;cells. &nbsp;There &nbsp;structure &nbsp;is&nbsp;&nbsp;like &nbsp;that &nbsp;of &nbsp;a &nbsp;cube. &nbsp;They &nbsp;form &nbsp;the &nbsp;inner &nbsp;lining &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;kidney. &nbsp;A&nbsp;times &nbsp;Cuboidal &nbsp;epithelium &nbsp;fold &nbsp;to &nbsp;for &nbsp;glandular &nbsp;epithelium.</p>\n\n<p><strong>b) Connective &nbsp;tissue :</strong></p>\n\n<p>In &nbsp;case &nbsp;of &nbsp;connective &nbsp;tissues, &nbsp;the &nbsp;cells &nbsp;are &nbsp;loosely &nbsp;packed &nbsp;and &nbsp;lie &nbsp;in &nbsp;a &nbsp;intercellular &nbsp;matrix.</p>\n\n<p>Eg : Blood &nbsp;cells. In &nbsp;blood &nbsp;cell, &nbsp;the &nbsp;matrix &nbsp;is &nbsp;plasma. &nbsp;The &nbsp;cells &nbsp;that &nbsp;lie &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;matrix &nbsp;are &nbsp;RBCs, &nbsp;WBCs &nbsp;and &nbsp;platelets. Blood &nbsp;helps &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;transportation &nbsp;of &nbsp;gases, &nbsp;hormones, &nbsp;waste &nbsp;products &nbsp;and &nbsp;even &nbsp;digested &nbsp;food &nbsp;particles.</p>\n\n<p>Bone &nbsp;is &nbsp;also &nbsp;a &nbsp;type &nbsp;of &nbsp;connective &nbsp;tissue. The &nbsp;matrix &nbsp;that &nbsp;rests &nbsp;the &nbsp;bone &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;rich &nbsp;compound &nbsp;made &nbsp;of &nbsp;calcium &nbsp;and &nbsp;phosphorus. &nbsp;The &nbsp;ligament &nbsp;that &nbsp;inter &nbsp;connects &nbsp;the &nbsp;bone &nbsp;is &nbsp; also &nbsp;a &nbsp;connective &nbsp;tissue. &nbsp;Bones &nbsp;provides &nbsp;basic &nbsp;framework &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;body &nbsp;and &nbsp;ligments &nbsp;along &nbsp;with &nbsp;tendens &nbsp;provide &nbsp;flexibility.</p>\n\n<p>Cartilage , &nbsp;Which &nbsp;is &nbsp;also &nbsp;a &nbsp;connective &nbsp;tissue &nbsp;is &nbsp;present &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;matrix &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;sugars &nbsp;and &nbsp;proteins. &nbsp;Cartilage &nbsp;gets &nbsp;as &nbsp;softbone &nbsp;at &nbsp;the &nbsp;surface &nbsp;or &nbsp;apex &nbsp;of &nbsp;bone &nbsp;surfaces.Its &nbsp;present &nbsp;in &nbsp;ear, &nbsp;nose, trachea &nbsp;etc.</p>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;space &nbsp;around &nbsp;the &nbsp;organs &nbsp;is &nbsp;filled &nbsp;by &nbsp;aerolar &nbsp;tissue.Aerolar &nbsp;connective &nbsp;tissue &nbsp;is &nbsp;found &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;skin &nbsp;and &nbsp;muscles, &nbsp;bone &nbsp;narrow &nbsp;etc &nbsp;and &nbsp;helps &nbsp;in &nbsp;repairing &nbsp;the &nbsp;party &nbsp;damaged &nbsp;tissue.</p>\n\n<p>Adipose &nbsp;tissue &nbsp;are &nbsp;tissue &nbsp;that &nbsp;store &nbsp;fat. &nbsp;These &nbsp;are &nbsp;present &nbsp;below &nbsp;skin. &nbsp;As &nbsp;stated, &nbsp;their &nbsp;main &nbsp;function &nbsp;is &nbsp;storage.</p>\n\n<p><strong>c) Muscular &nbsp;tissue :</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>Muscles &nbsp;are &nbsp;composed &nbsp;of &nbsp;different &nbsp;types &nbsp;of &nbsp;muscular &nbsp;tissues. Muscles &nbsp;are &nbsp;fibroes &nbsp;in &nbsp;nature &nbsp;and &nbsp;contain &nbsp;action &nbsp;and &nbsp;neyosin &nbsp;proteins &nbsp;that &nbsp;help &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;contraction &nbsp;and &nbsp;relaxation &nbsp;of &nbsp;muscles.The &nbsp;muscles &nbsp;that &nbsp;are &nbsp;attached &nbsp;to &nbsp;bones &nbsp;are &nbsp;called &nbsp;as &nbsp;skeletal &nbsp;muscles. &nbsp;A &nbsp;muscle &nbsp;cell &nbsp;will show &nbsp;bands - dark &nbsp;and &nbsp;light. &nbsp;These &nbsp;are &nbsp;called &nbsp;strained &nbsp;muscle &nbsp;fibres &nbsp;and &nbsp;look like &nbsp;cylinder. &nbsp;A &nbsp;part &nbsp;of &nbsp;straiked &nbsp;muscle &nbsp;fibres, &nbsp;there &nbsp;are &nbsp;smooth &nbsp;muscle fibres &nbsp;that &nbsp;help &nbsp;in &nbsp;movement of &nbsp;involuntary &nbsp;muscles &nbsp;like &nbsp;the &nbsp;muscles &nbsp;that &nbsp;is &nbsp;present &nbsp;in &nbsp;eyes. &nbsp;Some &nbsp;musculave &nbsp;tissues &nbsp;bear &nbsp;nucleus &nbsp;and &nbsp;are &nbsp;no