(113, 'inline_html', '<p>We &nbsp;know &nbsp;that &nbsp;bodies &nbsp;in &nbsp;motion &nbsp;need &nbsp;force &nbsp;to &nbsp;change &nbsp;velocity ( i . e &nbsp;either &nbsp;speed &nbsp;or &nbsp;direction &nbsp;of &nbsp;motion &nbsp;or &nbsp;both. ) &nbsp;In &nbsp;short &nbsp;acceleration &nbsp;is &nbsp;not &nbsp;possible &nbsp;without &nbsp;force. This &nbsp;force &nbsp;can &nbsp;be &nbsp;mechanical &nbsp;force &nbsp;( push &nbsp;or &nbsp;pull ) &nbsp;or &nbsp;force &nbsp;developed &nbsp;by &nbsp;engines &nbsp;of &nbsp;automobiles.</p>\n\n<p>When &nbsp;you &nbsp;throw &nbsp;a &nbsp;ball &nbsp;or &nbsp;any &nbsp;object &nbsp;up &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;air , &nbsp;it &nbsp;goes &nbsp;up &nbsp;because &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;mechanical &nbsp;force &nbsp;applied &nbsp;by &nbsp;you. &nbsp;But &nbsp;the &nbsp;ball &nbsp;progressively &nbsp;slows &nbsp;every &nbsp;instant &nbsp;and &nbsp;after &nbsp;reaching &nbsp;some &nbsp;height &nbsp;it &nbsp;stops. &nbsp;Its &nbsp;speed &nbsp;is &nbsp;decreasing &nbsp;continuously &nbsp;or &nbsp;it &nbsp;is &nbsp;decelerating.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Then &nbsp;the &nbsp;ball &nbsp;changes &nbsp; its &nbsp;direction &nbsp;and &nbsp;begins &nbsp;to &nbsp; fall &nbsp;down &nbsp;towards &nbsp;the &nbsp;earth. &nbsp;As &nbsp;it &nbsp;falls &nbsp;its &nbsp;speed &nbsp;increases &nbsp;every &nbsp;instant &nbsp;or &nbsp;it &nbsp;accelerates. &nbsp;It &nbsp;must &nbsp;be &nbsp;clear &nbsp;to &nbsp;you &nbsp;now , &nbsp;that &nbsp;every &nbsp;moment &nbsp;during &nbsp;its &nbsp;motion , &nbsp;the &nbsp;ball &nbsp;is &nbsp;under &nbsp;some &nbsp;force &nbsp;other &nbsp;than &nbsp;the &nbsp;force &nbsp;you &nbsp;applied. Otherwise &nbsp;it &nbsp;wont &nbsp;have &nbsp;decelerated , it &nbsp;wont &nbsp;have &nbsp;changed &nbsp;its &nbsp;direction , &nbsp;it &nbsp;wont &nbsp;have &nbsp;accelerated &nbsp;while &nbsp;coming &nbsp;down. Just &nbsp;remember &nbsp;the &nbsp;ball &nbsp;is &nbsp;under &nbsp;some &nbsp;invisible &nbsp;force.</p>\n\n<p>