(4599, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;from &nbsp;point &nbsp;A &nbsp;to B &nbsp;in semicircle &nbsp;path &nbsp;of &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;14 m.</p>\n\n<p>Its &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;and &nbsp;distance &nbsp;are &nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Displacement is straight line joining &nbsp;AB&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The straight line is also the diameter of the semi circle&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Displacement &nbsp;= &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;= &nbsp;14 m.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;14 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Distance is length of actual path&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Here actual path is a saemi circle of &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;14 &nbsp;m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Hence it is half the circumference &nbsp;of &nbsp;a circle &nbsp;whose &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;is &nbsp;14 m.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Distance &nbsp;( s ) &nbsp;=&nbsp;$ \\frac{circumference}{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{2&nbsp;\\prod &nbsp;r}{2} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\frac{&nbsp;\\prod &nbsp;d}{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp; = &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{&nbsp;&nbsp;\\frac{22}{7} *14&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp; = &nbsp; 77 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp; = &nbsp; 77 m, &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;14 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', 'uploads/178b88139305f34bb6daa22046c19864.png', 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4600, '<p>A body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;along &nbsp;equilateral &nbsp;triangle &nbsp;of &nbsp;side &nbsp;10 &nbsp;cm as &nbsp;shown &nbsp; its distance &nbsp;and &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;are.......m</p>\n', '<p>distance (s) in length of actual path&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Here it is sum of 3 &nbsp;sides of equilateral &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;3 &nbsp;X &nbsp;10 &nbsp;cm</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; 3 X &nbsp;$ \\frac{10}{100} $ m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;0 . 3 m</p>\n\n<p>Initial position &nbsp;= &nbsp;A</p>\n\n<p>Final &nbsp;position &nbsp;= C</p>\n\n<p>The &nbsp; &nbsp;straight &nbsp; line &nbsp; joining &nbsp; &nbsp;AC is &nbsp;a side &nbsp;of &nbsp; equilateral &nbsp; &nbsp;traingle&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Displacement ( $ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;) &nbsp;= &nbsp;L ( AC )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;10 cm</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; =&nbsp;$ \\frac{10}{100} $ m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;0 .1 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;0 . 3 m &nbsp;, &nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;0 . 1 m</p>\n', 'uploads/320bb78d27465092ff2d5ccf5e25846c.png', 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4601, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves along a circle as shown &nbsp;from &nbsp;A &nbsp;to C. Find its distance and displacement if a diameter of circle is 14 m</p>\n', '<p>Distance : Here distance is &nbsp; $ \\frac{3}{4} $th circumference</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{2&nbsp;\\prod r&nbsp;}{3} $ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;d&nbsp; = 2 r</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s = &nbsp;$ \\frac{&nbsp;\\prod d&nbsp;}{3} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{ &nbsp;\\frac{22}{7}*21&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}{3} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{44}{3} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;11 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Join &nbsp; A and C &nbsp;with straight line&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>A &nbsp; = &nbsp;initial &nbsp;position</p>\n\n<p>C &nbsp;= &nbsp; final position</p>\n\n<p>Also &nbsp; draw &nbsp; radius &nbsp; AO &nbsp; along &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6em;">CD</span></p>\n\n<p>AO &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\frac{diame ter}{2} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{21}{2} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; OC &nbsp; = &nbsp;7 m</p>\n\n<p>AC is &nbsp;hypothesous of right &nbsp;$ \\triangle $ &nbsp;AOC</p>\n\n<p>Apply pythogorous theorem</p>\n\n<p>$ AC^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ AO^{2} $ &nbsp;+&nbsp;$ OC^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; =&nbsp;$ 7^{2} $ &nbsp;+&nbsp;$ 7^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = 49 &nbsp;+ &nbsp;49</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$ AC^{2} $ = 98</p>\n\n<p>AC &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\sqrt{98} $ &nbsp;m &nbsp; &nbsp;which is less than 10 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;11 m , &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $&nbsp;$ \\cong $ 10</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4602, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;along &nbsp;a circle &nbsp;as &nbsp;shown &nbsp;in &nbsp;figure, &nbsp;find &nbsp;distance &nbsp;and &nbsp;displcement,</p>\n\n<p>when &nbsp;the &nbsp;body &nbsp;comes &nbsp;back to a A after &nbsp;1 &nbsp;revoluation</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp;Distance</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s&nbsp; = &nbsp;circumference &nbsp;= &nbsp;2&nbsp;$ \\prod $ &nbsp;r &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\prod $ d</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{22}{7} $ X &nbsp;14 &nbsp;= &nbsp;44 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;44 m</p>\n\n<p>Displacement :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;After 1 revoluation, &nbsp;body &nbsp;comes &nbsp;back to starting &nbsp;point</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; initial &nbsp;position &nbsp;= &nbsp;final &nbsp;position</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>Ans : B</p>\n', NULL, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4603, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;along &nbsp;a circle &nbsp;as &nbsp;shown &nbsp;in &nbsp;figure, &nbsp;find &nbsp;distance &nbsp;and &nbsp;displcement,</p>\n\n<p>when &nbsp;the &nbsp;body &nbsp;comes &nbsp;back to a A after &nbsp;1 &nbsp;revoluation</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp;Distance</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s&nbsp; = &nbsp;circumference &nbsp;= &nbsp;2&nbsp;$ \\prod $ &nbsp;r &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\prod $ d</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{22}{7} $ X &nbsp;14 &nbsp;= &nbsp;44 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;44 m</p>\n\n<p>Displacement :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;After 1 revoluation, &nbsp;body &nbsp;comes &nbsp;back to starting &nbsp;point</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; initial &nbsp;position &nbsp;= &nbsp;final &nbsp;position</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>Ans : B</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4604, '<p>What &nbsp;happens &nbsp;to &nbsp;distance &nbsp;and &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;after &nbsp;5 &nbsp;revoluations</p>\n', '<p>Distance : &nbsp;In 1 &nbsp;revoluation, &nbsp;s &nbsp; = &nbsp; 2$ \\prod $ r &nbsp;= &nbsp;44 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;In &nbsp;5 &nbsp;revoluations, &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;5 &nbsp;X &nbsp;44</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;220 m</p>\n\n<p>Displacement :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;After &nbsp;5 &nbsp;revoluation &nbsp;or in &nbsp;general &nbsp;after &nbsp;n &nbsp;revoluations, &nbsp;intial &nbsp;and &nbsp;final &nbsp;positions &nbsp;are &nbsp;same</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Displacement &nbsp;of &nbsp;5 &nbsp;revoluations &nbsp; = &nbsp;zero</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;220, &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>Ans : D</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4605, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;due east &nbsp; 4 m, &nbsp;then &nbsp;due &nbsp;north &nbsp;3m. Its &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;and &nbsp;distance &nbsp;are ............... &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Distance &nbsp;= &nbsp;Length &nbsp;of &nbsp;actual &nbsp;path</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;AB + &nbsp;BC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; 4 + 3 = &nbsp;7 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;= 7 m</p>\n\n<p>Displacement ($ \\bar{s} $) :</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Initial position &nbsp;= &nbsp;A</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Final &nbsp;position &nbsp;= &nbsp;C</p>\n\n<p>Joining AC by straight lines &nbsp;give &nbsp;right $ \\bigtriangleup $ &nbsp;ABC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; AC&nbsp; is &nbsp;the &nbsp;hypotheris</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;When &nbsp;a &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;from &nbsp;east &nbsp;to &nbsp;north, &nbsp;it &nbsp;has &nbsp;to &nbsp;turns &nbsp;by &nbsp;$ 90^{0} $&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;L[AC}</p>\n\n<p>Apply &nbsp;pythagarous &nbsp;theorem</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; $ AC^{2} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ AB^{2} $ &nbsp;+ &nbsp;$ BC^{2} $&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ 4^{2} $ &nbsp;+ &nbsp;$ 3^{2} $&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;16 &nbsp;+9</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$ AC^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;25 &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;AC &nbsp; = &nbsp;5 m &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp; A</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4606, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;starts &nbsp;from &nbsp;A &nbsp;and &nbsp;moves &nbsp;to &nbsp;B &nbsp;and &nbsp;C &nbsp;in straight &nbsp; line &nbsp;as &nbsp;shown&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Find &nbsp;distance &nbsp;and &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;when &nbsp;it &nbsp;is &nbsp;at &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>1) &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p>2) &nbsp;C</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp;At &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Distance (s) &nbsp;= &nbsp;length (AB)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; &nbsp;10 &nbsp;m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Displacement &nbsp;($ \\bar{s} $) &nbsp;= &nbsp;length (AB)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; 10 m</p>\n\n<p>At B &nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;10 m &nbsp;[note : That &nbsp;it&nbsp; is&nbsp;straight &nbsp;line &nbsp;motion]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>At &nbsp;C</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Distance &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;L[AB] &nbsp; + &nbsp;L[BA] &nbsp; + &nbsp;&nbsp;L[AC]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; 10 m &nbsp;+ &nbsp;10m + &nbsp;5m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp; = &nbsp;25 m.</p>\n\n<p>Displacement &nbsp;(&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Initial position &nbsp;= &nbsp;A</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Final &nbsp;position &nbsp;= &nbsp;C</p>\n\n<p>Joining &nbsp;then, &nbsp;we &nbsp;get &nbsp;straight &nbsp;line &nbsp;AC displacement &nbsp;is a&nbsp;vector quantity . It has direction. &nbsp;it &nbsp;direction &nbsp;from &nbsp;A &nbsp;to &nbsp;B &nbsp;is &nbsp;taken &nbsp;positive, then &nbsp;from A &nbsp;to C &nbsp;has &nbsp;to be &nbsp;- ve</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;L[AC]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;- 5 m</p>\n\n<p>At C</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;25 m, &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;- 5 m</p>\n\n<p>Note : displacement &nbsp;can &nbsp;have &nbsp;- ve &nbsp;value</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4607, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;starts &nbsp;from &nbsp;A &nbsp;and &nbsp;moves &nbsp;to &nbsp;B &nbsp;then&nbsp;C &nbsp;and &nbsp;returns &nbsp;to &nbsp;point &nbsp;A, find &nbsp;s &nbsp;and &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Always &nbsp;remember, &nbsp;whenever &nbsp;a &nbsp;moving &nbsp;body &nbsp;comes &nbsp;bacck &nbsp;to its &nbsp;original &nbsp;position, &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;is &nbsp;zero</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>Distance &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;L[AB] + &nbsp;L[BA] &nbsp;+ &nbsp;L[AC] &nbsp; + &nbsp;L[CA]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; 10 m &nbsp;+ &nbsp;10 m &nbsp;+ &nbsp; 5m &nbsp;+ &nbsp;5m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; &nbsp;30 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;30 &nbsp;m , &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>We have &nbsp;seen &nbsp;in &nbsp;this problem, &nbsp;that &nbsp;distance &nbsp;is &nbsp;always &nbsp;positive &nbsp;irrespective &nbsp;of &nbsp;direction &nbsp;of &nbsp;motion &nbsp;where &nbsp;as, &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;can &nbsp;be &nbsp;+ve, &nbsp;zero&nbsp; &nbsp;or &nbsp; - ve &nbsp; depending &nbsp;on &nbsp;the &nbsp;direction &nbsp;and &nbsp;position.</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;:B&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4608, '<p>Observe &nbsp;the &nbsp; following &nbsp; route &nbsp;taken &nbsp; by &nbsp;moving &nbsp; body &nbsp; and &nbsp;find &nbsp; its &nbsp; distance &nbsp;and &nbsp; displacement</p>\n', '<p>Always &nbsp;remember, &nbsp; distance &nbsp;is &nbsp;length &nbsp;of &nbsp;actual &nbsp;path.</p>\n\n<p>Displacement &nbsp;is &nbsp;length &nbsp;of &nbsp;straight &nbsp; line &nbsp;between &nbsp;initial &nbsp;and &nbsp;final &nbsp;points.</p>\n\n<p>s &nbsp;= &nbsp;L[AB] &nbsp;+ &nbsp;L[BC] &nbsp;+ &nbsp;L[CD] &nbsp; + &nbsp;L[DE] &nbsp; + &nbsp;&nbsp;L[EA] &nbsp; &nbsp;+ &nbsp;&nbsp;L[FG]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; &nbsp;4 m &nbsp;+ &nbsp; 3 m &nbsp; + &nbsp; 7m &nbsp; +&nbsp;8&nbsp;m &nbsp;+ &nbsp; 5&nbsp;m &nbsp; + &nbsp; 5m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp; 32 &nbsp;m</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;L[AG]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;L[AC] &nbsp; + &nbsp;L[CE] &nbsp;+ &nbsp;&nbsp;L[EG]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;5 m &nbsp;+ &nbsp;10 m &nbsp; + &nbsp;8 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp; 23 m</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: A</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
