(4625, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;from &nbsp;A &nbsp;to &nbsp;B &nbsp;as &nbsp;shown &nbsp;in &nbsp; figure. &nbsp; Find &nbsp;its &nbsp;speed &nbsp; and &nbsp;velocity [ &nbsp;v &nbsp; and &nbsp;$ \\bar{v} $ ] &nbsp;in &nbsp;m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp; Speed ( v) &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{distance( s )}{time ( t )} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{l(AB)}{10 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{l(100 m)}{10 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;10 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;v &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; &nbsp;10 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Velocity ($ \\bar{v} $) &nbsp;=&nbsp;$ \\frac{displacement( &nbsp;\\bar{s} &nbsp;&nbsp;)}{time ( t )} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp; straight &nbsp;line &nbsp;distance &nbsp;between &nbsp;starting &nbsp; and &nbsp; and &nbsp;end &nbsp;point</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp; &nbsp;l ( AB )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bar{v} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{l(AB)}{10 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{l(100 m)}{10 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;10 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{v} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;10 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>This &nbsp;example &nbsp; tells &nbsp;us &nbsp; that &nbsp;when &nbsp;a &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;in straight &nbsp;line , magnitude &nbsp;of &nbsp;speed and &nbsp;velocity are equal. &nbsp;This is &nbsp;because magnitude &nbsp;of &nbsp;distance &nbsp;and &nbsp;displacements &nbsp; are &nbsp;also &nbsp;same</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4626, '<p>A &nbsp; body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;along &nbsp;a &nbsp;semicircle &nbsp;of &nbsp;radius &nbsp;7 m &nbsp; from &nbsp; A &nbsp; to &nbsp;B &nbsp; in &nbsp;10 s. &nbsp;Its &nbsp;speed &nbsp;and &nbsp;velocity &nbsp;are .......... m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp;Speed ( v ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{s}{t} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{circumference}{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{2&nbsp;\\prod r&nbsp;}{2} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{2 * &nbsp;\\frac{22}{7} *7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;22 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;v &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{22 m}{5 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp; 4 . 4m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Velocity ( $ \\bar{v} $ ) &nbsp;=&nbsp;$ \\frac{&nbsp;\\bar{ s&nbsp;} }{t} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;l &nbsp;(AB) &nbsp;= &nbsp;diameter</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;d &nbsp;= &nbsp;2 r &nbsp;= &nbsp;2 x 7 &nbsp;14 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Velocity&nbsp;(&nbsp;$ \\bar{v} $ ) &nbsp;=&nbsp;$ \\frac{14 m&nbsp;}{5 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;2 . 8&nbsp;m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: D</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4627, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;along &nbsp; circumference &nbsp;of &nbsp;a &nbsp;circle &nbsp;of &nbsp;radius &nbsp;7 m &nbsp;at &nbsp;constant speed of &nbsp;11 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $ . It completes &nbsp;10 &nbsp;revolutions &nbsp;in &nbsp;time ......... s&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>In &nbsp;one&nbsp; revoluation, &nbsp;distance (s) covered &nbsp;is &nbsp;equal &nbsp;to &nbsp;circumference &nbsp; of &nbsp;the &nbsp;circle &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;2&nbsp;$ \\prod $ r &nbsp; in 1 &nbsp;revoluation</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;2 &nbsp;X &nbsp;$ \\frac{22}{7} $ &nbsp;X &nbsp;7 &nbsp; = &nbsp;44 m</p>\n\n<p>Speed &nbsp;is &nbsp;given &nbsp; 11 m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; t &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{s}{v} $ &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; [v &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{s}{t} $]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; t &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{44 m}{11 ms^{-1}&nbsp;} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;4 s</p>\n\n<p>It completes &nbsp;1 &nbsp;revolution &nbsp;in &nbsp;4s</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;It &nbsp; will &nbsp;take &nbsp;10 &nbsp;X &nbsp;4s &nbsp;= &nbsp;40 s &nbsp;to &nbsp;complete 10 &nbsp;revolution.</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;C</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
