(4634, '<p>A &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;along a &nbsp;rectangular path &nbsp;ABCD as shown &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>It &nbsp;takes &nbsp;2s &nbsp;to &nbsp;move &nbsp;from A &nbsp;to B &nbsp;and &nbsp;more &nbsp;1s &nbsp;to &nbsp;move &nbsp;from &nbsp;B &nbsp;to &nbsp;C. &nbsp;Its &nbsp;speed &nbsp; and &nbsp;velocity &nbsp;when &nbsp;it &nbsp;reaches &nbsp;C are .........m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp; Speed ( v ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{total &nbsp;distance (s)}{total &nbsp;time (t)} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{4 m + 3 m}{2 s + 1 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{7}{3} $m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;v &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{7}{3} $m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Velocity ($ \\bar{v} $ ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{displacement (&nbsp;\\bar{v})&nbsp;}{time ( t)&nbsp;} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Initial &nbsp;position &nbsp; = &nbsp;A</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Final &nbsp;position &nbsp;= &nbsp;C</p>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;straight &nbsp;line &nbsp;AC &nbsp;whose &nbsp;length &nbsp;gives &nbsp;magnitude &nbsp; of &nbsp; displacement &nbsp; is &nbsp; also &nbsp;hypothereous &nbsp;of &nbsp;right&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $ AC^{2} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ AB^{2} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;+ &nbsp; &nbsp;$ BC^{2} $&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ 4^{2} $ &nbsp;+ &nbsp;&nbsp;$ 3^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; 16 &nbsp; + &nbsp; &nbsp;9</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ AC^{2} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp; 25</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;AC&nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; $ \\sqrt{25} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;5