(4771, '<p>Consider &nbsp;a &nbsp;body &nbsp;moving &nbsp;along &nbsp;a &nbsp;circle &nbsp;of &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;28 m</p>\n\n<p><img alt="" src="/ckfinder/userfiles/images/56_quest.png" style="height:342px; width:370px" /></p>\n\n<p>It &nbsp;moves &nbsp;with &nbsp;uniform &nbsp;speed &nbsp;to &nbsp;complete &nbsp;1 &nbsp;revolution &nbsp;in &nbsp;22 s. &nbsp;Its &nbsp;speed &nbsp;and &nbsp;velocity &nbsp;at &nbsp;point &nbsp;B &nbsp;are</p>\n', '<p>As &nbsp;it &nbsp;is &nbsp;moving &nbsp;with &nbsp;uniform &nbsp;or &nbsp;constant &nbsp;speed , &nbsp;The &nbsp;body &nbsp;will have &nbsp;same &nbsp;speed &nbsp;at &nbsp;all points &nbsp;on &nbsp;the &nbsp;circle .</p>\n\n<p>Let &nbsp;us &nbsp;find &nbsp;that &nbsp;uniform &nbsp;speed</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;v &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{distance( s )}{time} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;circumference &nbsp;[ &nbsp;for &nbsp;1 &nbsp;revolutions ]</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;s &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\prod $ &nbsp;d</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{22}{7} $ X &nbsp;28 m &nbsp;= &nbsp;88m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; s &nbsp;= &nbsp;88 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Given &nbsp;t &nbsp;= &nbsp;22&nbsp;s</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Speed ( v) &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{88 m}{22 s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;4 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>At &nbsp;point &nbsp;B , as &nbsp;well &nbsp;as &nbsp;every where,&nbsp; &nbsp;speed &nbsp;is &nbsp;4 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Velocity &nbsp;(&nbsp;$ \\bar{v} $ ) &nbsp;at &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p><img alt="" src="/ckfinder/userfiles/images/56_sol.png" style="height:278px; width:300px" /></p>\n\n<p>Initial &nbsp;position &nbsp;= &nbsp;A</p>\n\n<p>Final &nbsp;position &nbsp; = &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p>l ( AB ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;magnitude &nbsp;of &nbsp;displacement</p>\n\n<p>Join &nbsp;A &nbsp;and &nbsp;B &nbsp;by &nbsp;straight &nbsp;line.</p>\n\n<p>AB &nbsp;is &nbsp;hyp &nbsp;of &nbsp;right &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ &nbsp;AOB</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ AB^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ AO^{2} $ &nbsp;+ &nbsp;$ OB^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;But &nbsp;AO &nbsp;= &nbsp;OB &nbsp;= &nbsp;radius &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{diameter}{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;AO &nbsp;= &nbsp;OB &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{28 m}{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;14 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$ AB^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ 14^{2} $ &nbsp;+ &nbsp;&nbsp;$ 14^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;2 $(14)^{2}$</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;AB &nbsp; = &nbsp; 14&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{2} $ m.</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; 14&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{2} $ m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;t &nbsp;= &nbsp;?</p>\n\n<p>We &nbsp;know &nbsp;speed &nbsp;v &nbsp;= &nbsp;4 m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>When &nbsp;the &nbsp;body &nbsp;moves &nbsp;from &nbsp;A &nbsp;to &nbsp;B, &nbsp;along &nbsp;the &nbsp;circumference, &nbsp;it &nbsp;covers &nbsp;distance &nbsp;equal &nbsp;to &nbsp;length &nbsp;of &nbsp;arc &nbsp;AB.</p>\n\n<p>As &nbsp;it &nbsp;is &nbsp;equal &nbsp;to &nbsp;$ \\frac{1}{4} $ th &nbsp;of &nbsp;a circle, &nbsp;the &nbsp;distance &nbsp;between &nbsp;A &nbsp;and &nbsp;B is &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\frac{1}{4} $ &nbsp;th &nbsp;of &nbsp;circumference</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; s &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{88 m}{4} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp; 22 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; t &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{s}{v} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{22&nbsp;m}{4 ms^{-1}} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;5 . 5 s</p>\n\n<p>Velocity &nbsp;($ \\bar{v} $ ) &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{\\bar{s}}{t} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{14&nbsp;\\sqrt{2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;} &nbsp;}{5.5} $m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;2 .54&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{2} $&nbsp;m&nbsp;$ s^{-1} $</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(4772, '<p>Consider &nbsp;a &nbsp;body &nbsp;moving &nbsp;along &nbsp;a &nbsp;circle &nbsp;of &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;28 m.</p>\n\n<p><img alt="" src="/ckfinder/userfiles/images/56_quest(1).png" style="height:231px; width:250px" /></p>\n\n<p>It &nbsp;moves &nbsp;with &nbsp;uniform &nbsp;speed &nbsp;to &nbsp;complete &nbsp;1 &nbsp;revolution &nbsp;in &nbsp;22 s. &nbsp;Its &nbsp;speed &nbsp;and &nbsp;velocity &nbsp;at &nbsp;point &nbsp;C&nbsp; are</p>\n', '<p>Speed &nbsp;( v ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;4 m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n\n<p>As &nbsp;speed &nbsp;uniform , &nbsp;speed &nbsp;at &nbsp;B &nbsp;and &nbsp;C &nbsp;are &nbsp;same. we have &nbsp;already &nbsp;solved &nbsp;it &nbsp;for &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Velocity (&nbsp;$ \\bar{v} $ ) &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{\\bar{s}}{t} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Initial &nbsp;position &nbsp; = &nbsp;A</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Final &nbsp; position &nbsp;= &nbsp;C</p>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;straight &nbsp;AC &nbsp;which &nbsp;gives &nbsp;the &nbsp;magnitude &nbsp;of &nbsp;displacement &nbsp;is &nbsp;also &nbsp;the &nbsp;diameter &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;circle.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;l ( AC ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;28 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bar{s} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;28 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;t &nbsp;= &nbsp;?</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;t &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{s}{v} $</p>\n\n<p>s &nbsp;= &nbsp;arc &nbsp;ABC &nbsp;is &nbsp;half &nbsp;the &nbsp;circumference</p>\n\n<p>s &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{88}{2} $ &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;44 m</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; t &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{44 m}{4 m &nbsp;s^{-1} &nbsp;} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;11 s</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bar{v} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{&nbsp;\\bar{s} }{t} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ \\frac{28}{11} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;2 .54 &nbsp;m$ s^{-1} $</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
