(5095, '<p>Distance &nbsp;between &nbsp;two &nbsp;points &nbsp;A ( 4 , 10 ) &nbsp;and &nbsp;B ( 7 , - 6 ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;...........</p>\n', '<p>Distance &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\sqrt{&nbsp;(x_{2} -x_{1})^{2} + (y_{2} -y_{1})^{2}&nbsp;&nbsp;} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{&nbsp;(7 -4)^{2} + (-6 -10)^{2}&nbsp;&nbsp;} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\sqrt{&nbsp;(+3)^{2} + (-16)^{2}&nbsp;&nbsp;} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\sqrt{9+256} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\sqrt{265} $</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;C</p>\n', NULL, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5096, '<p>The &nbsp;point &nbsp;on &nbsp;x - axis &nbsp;which &nbsp;is &nbsp;equidistant &nbsp;from &nbsp;the &nbsp;points &nbsp;( 5 , 4 ) &nbsp;and &nbsp;&nbsp;( - 2&nbsp;, 3&nbsp;)</p>\n', '<p>Let &nbsp;the &nbsp;point &nbsp;P &nbsp;= &nbsp;( &nbsp;x&nbsp;, 0&nbsp;) , &nbsp;A &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;( 5 , 4 ) , &nbsp;B &nbsp;= &nbsp;( - 2&nbsp;, 3&nbsp;)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;AP &nbsp;= &nbsp;BP</p>\n\n<p>$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;$ (AP)^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ (BP)^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ (x-5)^{2} $+&nbsp;$ (0-4)^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$ (x+2)^{2} $+&nbsp;$ (0-3)^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;$ x^{2} $ - &nbsp;10x &nbsp;+ 25 + 16 &nbsp; = &nbsp;&nbsp;$&nbsp;x^{2} $ +&nbsp; 4x &nbsp;+ 4&nbsp;+ 9</p>\n\n<p>$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp; - 14x &nbsp;= &nbsp;- 28 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ x &nbsp;= &nbsp;2</p>\n\n<p>Point &nbsp;P&nbsp; = &nbsp;(&nbsp;&nbsp;x&nbsp;, 0&nbsp;) &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;( &nbsp;2&nbsp;, 0&nbsp;)</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: &nbsp;D</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5097, '<p>If &nbsp;the &nbsp;distance &nbsp;of &nbsp;P&nbsp;(&nbsp;&nbsp;x&nbsp;, y&nbsp;) &nbsp;from &nbsp;A&nbsp;( &nbsp;4&nbsp;, 2&nbsp;) &nbsp;and &nbsp;B ( &nbsp;-1&nbsp;, 3&nbsp;) &nbsp;are &nbsp;equal &nbsp;then</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp; P &nbsp;( &nbsp;x&nbsp;, y&nbsp;) , &nbsp;A &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;( 4&nbsp;, 2&nbsp;) , &nbsp;B &nbsp;= &nbsp;( - 1&nbsp;, 3&nbsp;) &nbsp;are &nbsp;given &nbsp;points.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AP &nbsp;= &nbsp;BP</p>\n\n<p>$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;$ (AP)^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ (BP)^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ (x-4)^{2} $+&nbsp;$ (y-2)^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$ (x+1)^{2} $+&nbsp;$ (y-3)^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;$ x^{2} $ - &nbsp;8x &nbsp;+ 16 &nbsp;+ $ y^{2} $ &nbsp;- &nbsp;4y &nbsp;+ &nbsp;4&nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$&nbsp;x^{2} $ + &nbsp;2x &nbsp;+ 2&nbsp;+ &nbsp;$ y^{2} $-&nbsp;6y &nbsp;+ &nbsp;9</p>\n\n<p>10x &nbsp;- &nbsp;2y &nbsp;= &nbsp;20 - &nbsp;11</p>\n\n<p>10x -&nbsp;2y &nbsp;= &nbsp;9</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: &nbsp;B</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5098, '<p>The &nbsp;distance &nbsp;from &nbsp;origin &nbsp;to &nbsp;the &nbsp;point &nbsp;( 5 , - 4 ) &nbsp;is ............. units</p>\n', '<p>Origin (O) &nbsp;= &nbsp;( 0&nbsp;, 0&nbsp;) &nbsp;point (A) &nbsp;= &nbsp;( 5 , - 4 )</p>\n\n<p><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6em;">Distance &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\sqrt{&nbsp;(5 -0)^{2} + (-4 -0)^{2}&nbsp;&nbsp;} $</span></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6em;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;</span>$ \\sqrt{25+16} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; =$ \\sqrt{41} $ units</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;A</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5099, '<p>If &nbsp;the &nbsp;distance &nbsp;between &nbsp;the &nbsp;points &nbsp;( x , 1 ) &nbsp;and &nbsp;( 2 , &nbsp;-3) &nbsp;is &nbsp;4 &nbsp;then &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>x &nbsp;= ......</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp; Points &nbsp;( x , 1 ) &nbsp;,&nbsp; ( 2 , &nbsp;-3)</p>\n\n<p>Distance &nbsp;= &nbsp;4</p>\n\n<p>$ (x-2)^{2} $ +&nbsp;&nbsp;$ (1+3)^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ 4^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>$ x^{2} $ - &nbsp;4x + 4 + 16 &nbsp;= &nbsp;16</p>\n\n<p>$ x^{2} $ - &nbsp;4x&nbsp;+ 4 &nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>$ (x-2)^{2} $&nbsp;&nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>x &nbsp;= &nbsp;2</p>\n\n<p>Ans : C</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5100, '<p>The &nbsp;distance &nbsp;between &nbsp;two &nbsp;points &nbsp;is &nbsp;1 , &nbsp;one &nbsp;of &nbsp;them &nbsp;( 2 , 4 ) &nbsp;and &nbsp;the &nbsp;ordinate &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;second &nbsp;is &nbsp;3 &nbsp;then &nbsp;x &nbsp;co-ordinate &nbsp;is ...............</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp;Let &nbsp;A = &nbsp;( 2&nbsp;, 4&nbsp;) &nbsp;,&nbsp; ( x&nbsp;, &nbsp;-3)</p>\n\n<p>Distance &nbsp;= &nbsp;1</p>\n\n<p>$ (x-2)^{2} $ +&nbsp;&nbsp;$ (3-4)^{2} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ 1^{2} $</p>\n\n<p>$ x^{2} $ - &nbsp;4x + 4 + 1&nbsp; = &nbsp;1</p>\n\n<p>$ x^{2} $ - &nbsp;4x&nbsp;+ 4 &nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>$ (x-2)^{2} $&nbsp;&nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>x &nbsp;= &nbsp;2</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;B</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
