(5121, '<p>If &nbsp;A ( 3 , 2 ) &nbsp;and &nbsp;B ( -2 , 1 ) &nbsp;are &nbsp;two &nbsp;vertices &nbsp;of &nbsp;a &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ &nbsp;ABC , &nbsp;whose &nbsp;centroid &nbsp;is &nbsp;(&nbsp;$ \\frac{5}{3} $ ,&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{-1}{3} $ ). &nbsp;Then &nbsp;C &nbsp;= &nbsp;...........</p>\n', '<p>Let &nbsp;the &nbsp;third &nbsp;vertex &nbsp;C &nbsp;= &nbsp;( $ x_{3} $ &nbsp;,&nbsp;$ y_{3} $&nbsp;&nbsp;)</p>\n\n<p>A&nbsp;(&nbsp;$ x_{1} $&nbsp;&nbsp;,&nbsp;$ y_{1} $&nbsp;&nbsp;) &nbsp;= &nbsp;( 3 , 2 )</p>\n\n<p>B (&nbsp;$ x_{2} $&nbsp;&nbsp;,&nbsp;$ y_{2} $&nbsp;&nbsp;) &nbsp;= &nbsp;( -2&nbsp;, 1&nbsp;) &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>G &nbsp;= &nbsp;(&nbsp;$ \\frac{5}{3} $ ,&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{-1}{3} $ )</p>\n\n<p>($ \\frac{x_{1}+x_{2}+x_{3}}{3} $ , &nbsp;$ \\frac{y_{1}+y_{2}+y_{3}}{3} $) &nbsp;= &nbsp;(&nbsp;$ \\frac{5}{3} $ ,&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{-1}{3} $ )</p>\n\n<p>$ \\frac{x_{1}+x_{2}+x_{3}}{3} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\frac{5}{3} $</p>\n\n<p>3 - 2 +&nbsp;$ x_{3} $ &nbsp;= 5</p>\n\n<p>$ x_{3} $ &nbsp;= 4</p>\n\n<p>$ \\frac{y_{1}+y_{2}+y_{3}}{3} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\frac{-1}{3} $</p>\n\n<p>2 + 1 +&nbsp;$ y_{3} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;-1</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;$ y_{3} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;- 4</p>\n\n<p>C &nbsp;= &nbsp;(&nbsp;$ x_{3} $&nbsp;&nbsp;,&nbsp;$ y_{3} $&nbsp;&nbsp;) &nbsp;= &nbsp;( 4&nbsp;,&nbsp;- 4&nbsp;)</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;A</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
