(5144, '<p>The &nbsp;equation &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;line &nbsp;parallel &nbsp;to &nbsp;y - axis &nbsp;passing &nbsp;through &nbsp;the &nbsp;point &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;( - 4&nbsp;, - 5&nbsp;)&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;point &nbsp;= &nbsp;( - 4&nbsp;, - 5&nbsp;)&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Equation &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;line &nbsp;parallel &nbsp;to &nbsp;y - axis &nbsp;is &nbsp;x &nbsp;= k</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;x &nbsp;= &nbsp;- 4&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; x + 4 = 0</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;C</p>\n', NULL, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5145, '<p>One &nbsp;solution &nbsp;to &nbsp;2x - 5y &nbsp;= 10 &nbsp;is</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;equation &nbsp;is &nbsp;2x - 5y &nbsp;=&nbsp;10</p>\n\n<p>( 0 , - 2 ) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(0)&nbsp;- 5(-2)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;10 &nbsp;= &nbsp;10</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;( 0 , - 2 ) &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution</p>\n\n<p>( 1&nbsp;, &nbsp;2 ) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(1)&nbsp;- 5(2)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2 - 5 &nbsp;= &nbsp;10 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;- 3&nbsp; $ \\neq $ &nbsp; 10</p>\n\n<p>( 1&nbsp;, 2 ) &nbsp;is &nbsp;not &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution</p>\n\n<p>( -3&nbsp;,&nbsp;&nbsp;2 ) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(-3)&nbsp;- 5(2)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;- 6&nbsp;- 10&nbsp; = &nbsp;10&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;- 16&nbsp; $ \\neq $&nbsp;&nbsp; 10</p>\n\n<p>( - 3&nbsp;,&nbsp;2 ) &nbsp;is &nbsp;not &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution.</p>\n\n<p>( 4&nbsp;, &nbsp;-3&nbsp;) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(4)&nbsp;- 5(-3)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;8&nbsp;+&nbsp;15 &nbsp;= &nbsp;10&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;&nbsp;23&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\neq $&nbsp;&nbsp; 10</p>\n\n<p>( 4&nbsp;, -3&nbsp;) &nbsp;is &nbsp;not &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: A</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5146, '<p>Which &nbsp;is &nbsp;not &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution &nbsp;of &nbsp; 2x - 4y &nbsp;= &nbsp;10</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;equation &nbsp;is &nbsp;2x - 4y &nbsp;=&nbsp;10</p>\n\n<p>( 0 , $ \\frac{-5}{2} $ ) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(0)&nbsp;- 4($ \\frac{-5}{2} $)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;10 &nbsp;= &nbsp;10</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;( 0 , $ \\frac{-5}{2} $ ) &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution</p>\n\n<p>( 1&nbsp;, &nbsp;1&nbsp;) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(1)&nbsp;- 4(1)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$&nbsp; - 2&nbsp; $ \\neq $&nbsp;&nbsp; 10</p>\n\n<p>( 1&nbsp;, 1&nbsp;) &nbsp;is &nbsp;not &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution</p>\n\n<p>( 1&nbsp;, &nbsp;-2 ) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(1)&nbsp;- 4(-2)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp; 10&nbsp; = &nbsp;10 &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>( 1&nbsp;, -2 ) &nbsp;is&nbsp; a &nbsp;solution.</p>\n\n<p>( 2&nbsp;,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-3}{2} $ ) &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;2(2)&nbsp;- 4($ \\frac{-3}{2} $)&nbsp; =&nbsp;10 &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ 10&nbsp; = &nbsp;10 &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>( 2&nbsp;,&nbsp;$ \\frac{-3}{2} $ ) &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;solution</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: B</p>\n', NULL, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5147, '<p>Bhargavi &nbsp;got &nbsp;10 &nbsp;more &nbsp;marks &nbsp;than &nbsp;double &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;marks &nbsp;of &nbsp;sindhu &nbsp;in &nbsp;linear &nbsp;form&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Let &nbsp;sindhu&#39; s &nbsp;marks &nbsp;= &nbsp;x</p>\n\n<p>Bhargavi&#39; s &nbsp;marks &nbsp;= &nbsp;y</p>\n\n<p>By &nbsp;the &nbsp;sum &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;y &nbsp;= &nbsp;2x + 10</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;2x - y + 10 = 0</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;A</p>\n', NULL, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5148, '<p>The &nbsp;sum &nbsp;of &nbsp;a &nbsp;two &nbsp;digit &nbsp;number &nbsp;and &nbsp;the &nbsp;number &nbsp;obtained &nbsp;by &nbsp;reversing &nbsp;the &nbsp;order &nbsp;of &nbsp;its &nbsp;digits &nbsp;is &nbsp;121. &nbsp;Express &nbsp;in &nbsp;linear &nbsp;form &nbsp;if &nbsp;the &nbsp;digits &nbsp;in &nbsp;units &nbsp;and &nbsp;ten&#39;s &nbsp;place &nbsp;are &nbsp;x &nbsp;and &nbsp;y &nbsp;respectively.&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Let &nbsp;the &nbsp;number &nbsp;= &nbsp;10y + x</p>\n\n<p>Number &nbsp;obtained &nbsp;by &nbsp;reversing &nbsp;its &nbsp;digits &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;10x&nbsp;+ y</p>\n\n<p>Sum &nbsp; = &nbsp; (10y + x) &nbsp;+ &nbsp;(10x&nbsp;+ y)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = &nbsp; 11x &nbsp;+ &nbsp;11y</p>\n\n<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;11x &nbsp;+ &nbsp;11y &nbsp;= &nbsp;121</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;11( x + y ) &nbsp;= &nbsp;121</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; x + y &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{121}{11} $</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;x + y &nbsp;= &nbsp;11</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;D</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5149, '<p>A &nbsp;stone &nbsp;is &nbsp;falling &nbsp;from &nbsp;a &nbsp;mountain. &nbsp;The &nbsp;velocity &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;stone &nbsp;is &nbsp;given &nbsp;by &nbsp;V &nbsp;= &nbsp;9 . 8 t&nbsp;. &nbsp;What &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;velocity &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;stone &nbsp;4 &nbsp;seconds &nbsp;after &nbsp;start.&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Velocity &nbsp;V &nbsp;= &nbsp;9 . 8 t &nbsp; &nbsp;( given )</p>\n\n<p>The &nbsp;velocity &nbsp;after &nbsp;4 &nbsp;seconds &nbsp;V &nbsp;= &nbsp;9 . 8 * 4</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; 39 . 2 m/sec</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;C</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5150, '<p>The &nbsp;parking &nbsp;charges &nbsp;of &nbsp;a &nbsp;car &nbsp;in &nbsp;Hyderabad &nbsp;Railway &nbsp;station &nbsp;for &nbsp;first &nbsp;two &nbsp;hours &nbsp;is &nbsp;50 rupees &nbsp;and &nbsp;10 rupees &nbsp;for &nbsp;each &nbsp;subsequent &nbsp;hour. Then &nbsp;an &nbsp;equation..........</p>\n', '<p>Let &nbsp;the &nbsp;total &nbsp;money &nbsp;paid &nbsp;= &nbsp;y rupees</p>\n\n<p>Parking &nbsp;charges &nbsp;for &nbsp;first &nbsp;two &nbsp;hours &nbsp;= &nbsp;50 &nbsp;rupees</p>\n\n<p>Total &nbsp;parking &nbsp;charges &nbsp;x &nbsp;hours &nbsp;@ &nbsp;10 &nbsp;rupees</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Per &nbsp;hour &nbsp; = &nbsp;50 + 10 (x - 2)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp; 50 + 10x - 20</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;= &nbsp;10 x &nbsp;+ 30</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; y &nbsp;= &nbsp;10 x &nbsp;+ 30</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;B</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5151, '<p>In &nbsp;a &nbsp;mixture &nbsp;of &nbsp;28 &nbsp;liters , &nbsp;the &nbsp;ratio &nbsp;of &nbsp;milk &nbsp;and &nbsp;water &nbsp;is &nbsp;5 : 2 .Find &nbsp;the &nbsp;quantity &nbsp;of &nbsp;milk &nbsp;in &nbsp;the &nbsp;mixture.</p>\n', '<p>Let &nbsp;the &nbsp;quantity &nbsp;of &nbsp;milk &nbsp;= &nbsp;x lit</p>\n\n<p>In &nbsp;mixture &nbsp;quantity &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;mixture &nbsp;= &nbsp;y lit</p>\n\n<p>Ratio &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;milk &nbsp;and &nbsp;water &nbsp;= &nbsp;5 : 2</p>\n\n<p>Sum &nbsp;of &nbsp;the &nbsp;terms &nbsp;of &nbsp;ratio &nbsp;= &nbsp;5 + 2 &nbsp;= &nbsp;7</p>\n\n<p>Quantity &nbsp;of &nbsp;milk &nbsp;x &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{5}{7} $ y lit&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;7x &nbsp;= &nbsp;5y</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;7x - 5y &nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;y &nbsp;= &nbsp;28 , &nbsp;x &nbsp;= &nbsp;?</p>\n\n<p>7x &nbsp; - &nbsp;5 (28) &nbsp;= &nbsp;0</p>\n\n<p>7x &nbsp;= &nbsp;140</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; x &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{140}{7} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;20 lit</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;A</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5152, '<p>A &nbsp;linear &nbsp;equation &nbsp;that &nbsp;converts &nbsp;Fahrenheit &nbsp;to &nbsp;Celsius &nbsp;F &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{9}{5} $C + 32. &nbsp;If &nbsp;the &nbsp;temparature &nbsp;is &nbsp;$ 30^{0} $c , then &nbsp;Fahrenheit &nbsp;temparature</p>\n', '<p>F &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{9}{5} $C + 32</p>\n\n<p>Given &nbsp;C &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ 30^{0} $c</p>\n\n<p>F &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{9}{5}*30 $&nbsp;+ 32 &nbsp;= &nbsp;54 + 32 &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ 86^{0}F $</p>\n\n<p>Ans : C</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5153, '<p>A &nbsp;linear &nbsp;equation &nbsp;that &nbsp;converts &nbsp;Fahrenheit &nbsp;to &nbsp;Celsius &nbsp;F &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{9}{5} $C + 32. &nbsp;If &nbsp;the &nbsp;temparature &nbsp;is &nbsp;$ 95^{0}F $, &nbsp;then &nbsp;temparature &nbsp;in &nbsp;celsius ?</p>\n', '<p>F &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{9}{5} $C + 32</p>\n\n<p>Given &nbsp;F &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ 95^{0}F $</p>\n\n<p>$ 95^{0}F $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{9}{5} $C + 32</p>\n\n<p>$ \\frac{9}{5} $C &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ 95^{0}F $ &nbsp;- &nbsp;32 &nbsp;= &nbsp;63</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;C &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{63*5}{9} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ 35^{0}C&nbsp;$</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: &nbsp;D</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
