(5193, '<p>In &nbsp;a &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC , &nbsp;if &nbsp;AB &nbsp;= &nbsp;AC &nbsp;then &nbsp;$\\angle$B = ...........</p>\n', '<p>Ans : A</p>\n', NULL, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5194, '<p>In &nbsp;the &nbsp;given &nbsp;figure , $\\angle$B &lt; &nbsp;$\\angle$A &nbsp;and &nbsp;$\\angle$C&nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$D , &nbsp;then &nbsp;AD &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;...........</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$B &nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$A ; &nbsp;$\\angle$C &nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$D&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$B &nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$A &nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;AO &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;BO &nbsp; ( &nbsp;from &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ AOB ) ---------------(1)</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$C &nbsp;&lt;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$D&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;OD &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;OC &nbsp;( &nbsp;from &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ COD&nbsp;) ---------------(2)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Adding &nbsp;equation &nbsp;(1) &nbsp;and &nbsp;(2) &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;AO + OD &lt; &nbsp;OB + OC&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp; AD &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;BC</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: &nbsp;B</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5195, '<p>In &nbsp;the &nbsp;given &nbsp;figure , &nbsp;sides &nbsp;AB &nbsp;and &nbsp;AC &nbsp;of &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC &nbsp;are &nbsp;extended &nbsp;to &nbsp;points &nbsp;P &nbsp;and &nbsp;Q &nbsp;respectively. &nbsp;Also $\\angle$PBC &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;$\\angle$QCB. &nbsp;Then</p>\n', '<p>From &nbsp;the &nbsp;figure</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$PBC &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$A +&nbsp;$\\angle$ACB</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$QCB &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$A +&nbsp;$\\angle$ABC</p>\n\n<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$PBC &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;$\\angle$QCB</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6em;">$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;</span>&nbsp;$\\angle$A +&nbsp;$\\angle$ACB &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;$\\angle$A +&nbsp;$\\angle$ABC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;$\\angle$ACB &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;$\\angle$ABC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\Rightarrow$ &nbsp;AB &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;AC</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;D</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5196, '<p>In &nbsp;the &nbsp;given &nbsp;figure , &nbsp;PR &nbsp;&gt; &nbsp;PQ &nbsp;and &nbsp;PS &nbsp;bisects &nbsp;$\\angle$QPR. &nbsp;Then &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$PSQ ..............</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;&nbsp;PR &nbsp;&gt; &nbsp;PQ ; &nbsp;$\\angle$QPS&nbsp; = &nbsp;$\\angle$RPS</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;PR &nbsp;&gt; &nbsp;PQ</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$Q &nbsp;&gt; &nbsp;$\\angle$R</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$Q &nbsp;+ &nbsp;$\\angle$QPS &nbsp;&gt; &nbsp;$\\angle$R &nbsp;+&nbsp;$\\angle$RPS&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>$ 180^{0} $ &nbsp;- &nbsp;($\\angle$Q &nbsp;+ &nbsp;$\\angle$QPS) &nbsp;&gt; $ 180^{0} $ -&nbsp; ($\\angle$R &nbsp;+&nbsp;$\\angle$RPS)&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$PSQ &nbsp;&lt; &nbsp;$\\angle$PSR</p>\n\n<p>Ans &nbsp;: &nbsp;A</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5197, '<p>In &nbsp;a .............. &nbsp;triangle , &nbsp;the &nbsp;hypotenuse &nbsp;is &nbsp;the &nbsp;longest &nbsp;side</p>\n', '<p>Ans : B</p>\n', NULL, 0, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5198, '<p>$ \\bigtriangleup $ &nbsp;ABC &nbsp;is &nbsp;an &nbsp;isosceles &nbsp;triangle &nbsp;in &nbsp;which &nbsp;AB = AC. &nbsp;Side &nbsp;BA &nbsp;is &nbsp;produced &nbsp;to &nbsp;D &nbsp;such that &nbsp; AD = &nbsp;AB. &nbsp;Then $\\angle$BCD &nbsp;is .............. angle</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;in &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ DBC ,</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;AB = AC , &nbsp;&nbsp;AD&nbsp;= AB</p>\n\n<p>In &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$ABC +&nbsp;$\\angle$ACB &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$DAC &nbsp; ( exterior &nbsp;angle ) ----------(1)</p>\n\n<p>In &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ACD</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$ADC +&nbsp;$\\angle$ACD&nbsp; = &nbsp;$\\angle$BAC &nbsp;------------------(2)</p>\n\n<p>Adding &nbsp;(1) and &nbsp;(2)</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$DAC +&nbsp;$\\angle$BAC &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$ABC +&nbsp;$\\angle$ACB +&nbsp;$\\angle$ADC +&nbsp;$\\angle$ACD</p>\n\n<p>$ 180^{0} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;2 &nbsp;(&nbsp;$\\angle$ACB +&nbsp;$\\angle$ACD)</p>\n\n<p>$ 180^{0} $ &nbsp;= &nbsp;2 &nbsp;(&nbsp;$\\angle$BCD)</p>\n\n<p>$\\angle$BCD &nbsp;= &nbsp;$ \\frac{180^{0}}{2} $ &nbsp; = &nbsp;$ 90^{0} $</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;C</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5199, '<p>$ \\bigtriangleup $ABC &nbsp; is &nbsp;an &nbsp;isosceles &nbsp;triangle &nbsp;in &nbsp;which &nbsp;AB &nbsp;= &nbsp;AC &nbsp;then</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ABC &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;isosceles &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>and &nbsp;AB &nbsp;= &nbsp;AC</p>\n\n<p>Let &nbsp;D &nbsp;be &nbsp;the &nbsp;mid &nbsp;point &nbsp;of &nbsp;BC</p>\n\n<p>Join &nbsp;A , D , &nbsp;In &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ABD &nbsp;and &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ACD</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;AB &nbsp;= &nbsp;AC &nbsp;( given )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;BD &nbsp;= &nbsp;DC &nbsp;( construction )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; AD &nbsp;= &nbsp;AD &nbsp;( common )</p>\n\n<p>$ \\bigtriangleup $ABD &nbsp;$ \\cong $ &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ACD &nbsp; &nbsp; ( SSS &nbsp;congruence )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$B &nbsp;=&nbsp; $\\angle$C</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5200, '<p>PQR &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;right &nbsp;angled &nbsp;triangle &nbsp;in &nbsp;which &nbsp;$\\angle$P&nbsp; = &nbsp;$ 90^{0} $ &nbsp;and &nbsp;PQ &nbsp;= &nbsp;PR , &nbsp;then</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $PQR &nbsp;is &nbsp;right &nbsp;angled &nbsp;triangle</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; PQ &nbsp;= &nbsp;PR</p>\n\n<p>Join &nbsp;the &nbsp;mid point &nbsp;S &nbsp;of &nbsp;RQ</p>\n\n<p>Now &nbsp;in &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $PSR &nbsp;and &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $PSQ</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; PS &nbsp;= &nbsp;PS &nbsp;( common )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; PQ &nbsp;= &nbsp;PR &nbsp;( given )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;RS &nbsp;= &nbsp;SQ &nbsp;(construction )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $PSR &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\cong $ &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $PSQ</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$R&nbsp; =&nbsp; $\\angle$Q</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; Ans &nbsp;: &nbsp;A</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5201, '<p>BE &nbsp;and &nbsp;CF &nbsp;are &nbsp;two &nbsp;equal &nbsp;altitudes &nbsp;of &nbsp;a &nbsp;triangle &nbsp;ABC , &nbsp;then &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC ............. triangle</p>\n', '<p>&nbsp;In &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC , &nbsp;altitude &nbsp;BE &nbsp;and &nbsp;CF &nbsp;are &nbsp;equal.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;In &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ BCE &nbsp;and &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ CBF</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; $\\angle$BEC &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$CFB &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ( given &nbsp;$ 90^{0} $ )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; BC &nbsp;= &nbsp;BC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; CF &nbsp;= &nbsp;BE &nbsp; (given)</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $&nbsp;BEC &nbsp;$ \\cong $ &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $&nbsp;CBF</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$\\angle$EBC &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$FCB</p>\n\n<p>These &nbsp;are &nbsp;also &nbsp;the &nbsp;interior &nbsp;angles &nbsp;opposite &nbsp;to &nbsp;sides &nbsp;AC &nbsp;and &nbsp;AB &nbsp;of &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AC &nbsp;= &nbsp;AB</p>\n\n<p>It &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;isosceles &nbsp;triangle.</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;D</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5202, '<p>In &nbsp;quadrilateral &nbsp;ABCD , &nbsp;AC &nbsp;= &nbsp;AD &nbsp;and &nbsp; AB &nbsp;bisects &nbsp; $\\angle$A . &nbsp;And&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC &nbsp;$ \\cong $ &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABD &nbsp;then &nbsp;BC &nbsp;= &nbsp;............</p>\n', '<p>In &nbsp;a &nbsp;quadrilateral &nbsp;ABCD</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$\\overline{AC}$ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\overline{AD}$</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\overline{AB}$ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\overline{AB}$ &nbsp; ( common &nbsp;side )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$BAC &nbsp;= &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$BAD &nbsp;( &nbsp;AB &nbsp;bisects &nbsp;&nbsp;$\\angle$A )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABC &nbsp;$ \\cong $ &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ABD &nbsp;( &nbsp;SAS &nbsp;axiom )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$\\overline{BC}$ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\overline{BD}$</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Ans &nbsp;: C</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
(5203, '<p>ABCD &nbsp;is &nbsp;a &nbsp;quadrilateral &nbsp;in &nbsp;which &nbsp;AD &nbsp;= &nbsp;BC &nbsp;and &nbsp;$\\angle$DAB &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$CBA , &nbsp;then &nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABD &nbsp;$ \\cong $ &nbsp;................</p>\n', '<p>Given &nbsp;that &nbsp; $\\overline{AD}$ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\overline{BC}$ &nbsp;,&nbsp;$\\angle$DAB &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$CBA</p>\n\n<p>In &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABD &nbsp;and &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ BAC</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$\\overline{AD}$ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\overline{BC}$ &nbsp; ( given )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;$\\angle$DAB &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\angle$CBA &nbsp;(given )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;$\\overline{AB}$ &nbsp;= &nbsp;$\\overline{AB}$ &nbsp;( common &nbsp;side )</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $ ABD &nbsp;$ \\cong $&nbsp;&nbsp;$ \\bigtriangleup $&nbsp;BAC &nbsp; ( &nbsp;SAS &nbsp;congruence )</p>\n\n<p>Ans : &nbsp;B</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', NULL, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'N', 8),
